-- article
INSERT INTO articles (id, title, abstract, content, image_url, status, category_id, is_premium, views, publish_date, author)
VALUES
	(UUID(), 'More plant protein, less animal protein tied to lower heart disease risk, not stroke', 'A study published in the American Journal of Clinical Nutrition evaluated the relationship between cardiovascular disease (CVD) and the dietary plant-to-animal protein (P:A) ratio through three large prospective cohort studies in the United States. Over a 30-year follow-up, findings revealed that a higher P:A ratio was associated with a reduced risk of total CVD and coronary artery disease (CAD), but not stroke. Substituting plant protein for animal protein significantly lowered the risk of CVD (18%) and CAD (24%). Although the optimal P:A ratio remains unclear, ratios of 0.5 or higher appeared beneficial, with potential further benefits at 0.76 or above for CAD prevention. Future research should focus on populations with higher plant protein intake to refine recommendations for CVD prevention.', '<div><div><p><em> <strong> A higher plant-to-animal dietary protein ratio is associated with lower risks of cardiovascular disease and coronary artery disease, but not stroke </strong> </em></p><figure><img title="Study: Dietary plant-to-animal protein ratio and risk of cardiovascular disease in 3 prospective cohorts. Image Credit: 5PH/Shutterstock.com" src="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/images/news/ImageForNews_797593_17334979170824860.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 673px, (min-width: 1090px) 667px, (min-width: 992px) calc(66.6vw - 60px), (min-width: 480px) calc(100vw - 40px), calc(100vw - 30px)" srcset="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241206101158/ri/1000/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797593_17334979170824860.jpg 1000w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241206101158/ri/950/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797593_17334979170824860.jpg 950w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241206101158/ri/750/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797593_17334979170824860.jpg 750w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241206101158/ri/550/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797593_17334979170824860.jpg 550w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241206101158/ri/450/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797593_17334979170824860.jpg 450w" alt="Top view of legumes, beans, lentils, nuts, soy milk, tofu, cereals, seeds and sprouts on black table" width="1000" height="667" /><figcaption><em> Study:&nbsp; <a href="https://ajcn.nutrition.org/article/S0002-9165(24)00737-8/fulltext" rel="noopener"> Dietary plant-to-animal protein ratio and risk of cardiovascular disease in 3 prospective cohorts </a> . Image Credit: 5PH/Shutterstock.com </em></figcaption></figure><p>A recent&nbsp; <a href="https://ajcn.nutrition.org/article/S0002-9165(24)00737-8/fulltext" rel="noopener"> <em> American Journal of Clinical Nutrition </em> </a> &nbsp;study conducted a prospective cohort study to assess the relationship between cardiovascular disease and dietary plant-to-animal protein ratio.</p><h2>Dietary protein intake and the risk of cardiovascular disease</h2><p>In the United States, cardiovascular disease (CVD) is one of the leading causes of death, and international clinical practice guidelines, such as Canada&rsquo;s Food Guide and the EAT-Lancet Commission suggest replacing some animal protein in the diet with plant protein to lower the risk of CVD. Despite this, in developed countries, most protein is derived from animal sources. In the US, the ratio of plant-to-animal (P: A) protein ratio in the diet is approximately 1:3.</p><p>Research has not yet documented the optimal ratio of animal and plant protein intake in the diet for CVD prevention. The lack of evaluation of the optimal ratio has led to an absence of recommendations concerning the relative contribution from these sources of protein. Therefore, public health guidance on protein sources can be refined by assessing ratios of the plant-to-animal protein.</p><h2>About the study</h2><p>To address the above-mentioned gap in the literature, three large US prospective cohort studies were conducted to evaluate the relationship between different deciles of plant-to-animal protein and CVD, including dose-response relationships. Statistical substitution models were used to assess CVD risk by replacing the top animal protein sources with plant protein sources. This helped account for the fact that diets with the same plant-to-animal protein ratio could include different protein sources.</p><p>The three prospective cohort studies were the Nurses&rsquo; Health Study (NHS), NHSII, and Health Professionals Follow-up Study (HPFS). Hazard ratios (HRs) for CVD outcomes were estimated using multivariable-adjusted Cox proportional hazard models for 89,205 females in the NHSII (1991&ndash;2017), 70,918 females in the NHS (1984&ndash;2016), and 42,740 males from the HPFS (1986&ndash;2016). The percent energy from plant and animal protein was used to compute the P: A ratio. To determine the intake, a food frequency questionnaire (FFQ) was administered every 4 years.</p><p>CVD was defined as a composite of CAD, incident non-fatal myocardial infarction (MI), and fatal and non-fatal stroke. Death was confirmed by the National Death Index, relatives, or postal authorities. An array of covariates was considered, including medical history, family history, lifestyle, reproductive factors, medication use, and so on.</p><h2>Study findings</h2><p>During a 30-year follow-up, the median P: A ratio increased from about 0.36 to about 0.50. The cumulative average ratio ranged between 0.15 and 1.84, and, over the follow-up, the median calorie density from total protein remained consistent at around the 17%&ndash;19% range. As a percentage of total caloric intake, animal protein reduced from about 13% to about 11%, while the fraction of plant protein increased from about 5% to about 6%.</p><p>Overall, a lower risk of total CVD and CAD, but not stroke, was associated with a higher P: A ratio. The findings were insignificant for the NHSII cohort. The results were consistent in the pooled analyses, where a 1-standard deviation increase in the P: A ratio (~0.18) was associated with a lower risk of total CVD and CAD but not stroke. The findings for ischemic and hemorrhagic strokes were insignificant.</p><p>Concerning the dose dependence, a significant risk reduction was noted early in the dose-response curve, followed by more gradual reductions. For stroke, no evidence of linear or nonlinear associations was noted. When higher P: A ratios were combined with higher protein density, the inverse associations with CVD and CAD were stronger. The results were largely consistent in sensitivity and sub-group analyses. In a substitution analysis, when energy from plant protein was used to replace 3% energy from animal protein, a significant reduction in the risk of CVD (18%) and CAD (24%) was noted, but not for stroke.</p><p>It was not possible to determine the optimal P: A ratio for CVD risk reduction owing to the possible different dose-response relationships for stroke and CAD. However, it was noted that at around a P: A ratio of 0.5, the risk for both CVD and stroke started to plateau or potentially increase. The ratio could be 0.76 or higher for the prevention of CAD.</p><h2>Conclusions</h2><p>The results suggest that a higher P: A ratio protein ratio is associated with a lower risk of CVD and CAD, but not stroke. The findings also indicate that plant protein consumption coupled with higher protein density may offer additional benefits in terms of cardiovascular health.</p><p>In the future, more research is needed to pin down the optimal P: A ratio for the prevention of CVD. Studies should also be conducted in populations where the consumption of plant protein, in general, is higher to understand the optimal ratio for the prevention of CAD and stroke.</p></div></div> ', 'https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241206101158/ri/1000/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797593_17334979170824860.jpg', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Nutrition'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Bob Smith')),
	(UUID(), 'Replacing carbohydrates with protein and fat improves cholesterol profiles in type 2 diabetes', 'A recent study published in The American Journal of Clinical Nutrition found that a carbohydrate-reduced, high-protein (CRHP) diet improves cholesterol profiles and reduces liver fat in individuals with type 2 diabetes (T2D), independent of weight loss. Conducted over six weeks, the CRHP diet showed significant benefits over a conventional diabetes diet, including reductions in fasting triglycerides, small-dense LDL particles, and intrahepatic triglycerides, along with an improved HDL2/HDL3 ratio. These findings highlight the potential of CRHP diets as effective interventions for managing T2D-associated dyslipidemia and metabolic dysfunction.', '<div><div><div><p><a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0002916524014254?via%3Dihub" rel="noopener"><img src="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/images/news/ImageForNews_797479_17334055232498946.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 673px, (min-width: 1090px) 667px, (min-width: 992px) calc(66.6vw - 60px), (min-width: 480px) calc(100vw - 40px), calc(100vw - 30px)" srcset="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241205083154/ri/2000/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797479_17334055232498946.jpg 2000w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241205083154/ri/1950/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797479_17334055232498946.jpg 1950w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241205083154/ri/1750/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797479_17334055232498946.jpg 1750w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241205083154/ri/1550/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797479_17334055232498946.jpg 1550w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241205083154/ri/1350/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797479_17334055232498946.jpg 1350w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241205083154/ri/1150/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797479_17334055232498946.jpg 1150w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241205083154/ri/950/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797479_17334055232498946.jpg 950w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241205083154/ri/750/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797479_17334055232498946.jpg 750w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241205083154/ri/550/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797479_17334055232498946.jpg 550w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241205083154/ri/450/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797479_17334055232498946.jpg 450w" alt="Study:&nbsp;Replacing dietary carbohydrate with protein and fat improves lipoprotein subclass profile and liver fat in type 2 diabetes independent of body weight: evidence from two randomized controlled trials. Image Credit:&nbsp;Elena Veselova/Shutterstock.com" width="2000" height="1333" /></a><em>Study:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0002916524014254?via%3Dihub" rel="noopener">Replacing dietary carbohydrate with protein and fat improves lipoprotein subclass profile and liver fat in type 2 diabetes independent of body weight: evidence from two randomized controlled trials</a>. Image Credit:&nbsp;Elena Veselova/Shutterstock.com</em></p><p>In a recent study published in&nbsp;<a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0002916524014254?via%3Dihub" rel="noopener"><em>The American Journal of Clinical Nutrition</em></a>, a group of researchers evaluated whether reducing dietary carbohydrates and increasing protein and fat improves lipoprotein subclass profiles in type 2 diabetes (T2D), independent of body weight changes.</p><h2>Background</h2><p>Adopting a healthier lifestyle is fundamental in managing T2D, with weight loss often emphasized. Traditional dietary recommendations focus on low-fat, high-carbohydrate diets, but emerging evidence suggests reducing carbohydrate intake may improve glycemic control and diabetic dyslipidemia.</p><p>Carbohydrate restriction can normalize triacylglycerol (TAG) and High-density lipoprotein (HDL) cholesterol but has variable effects on Low-density lipoprotein (LDL) cholesterol.</p><p>It may also reduce metabolic dysfunction-associated steatotic liver disease (MASLD), though findings remain inconclusive due to challenges like poor adherence and confounding factors like weight loss or exercise. Further research is needed to clarify the independent effects of carbohydrate restriction on lipid metabolism.</p><h2>About the study</h2><p>The two studies were conducted as open-label, prospective, randomized controlled trials (RCTs) at Copenhagen University Hospital Bispebjerg to evaluate the effects of a carbohydrate-reduced high-protein (CRHP) diet compared with a conventional diabetes (CD) diet over six weeks.</p><p>The Iso study involved a cross-over design with 30 participants maintaining stable weight, while the Hypo study utilized a parallel-group design with 72 participants aiming for a 6% weight loss. Both trials were approved by the local ethics committee and adhered to strict eligibility criteria.</p><p>Participants with T2D were included based on Hemoglobin A1c (HbA1c), levels between 48 and 97 mmol/mol (6.5&ndash;11%), while exclusions were made for conditions such as severe renal disease, anemia, critical illness, and certain medications.</p><div data-event-label="CHEMUK - Highlights from 2023, Rel: Secondary, Loc: Content. Comp: 17 items" data-event-logged="true"><div><div><a href="https://www.news-medical.net/industry-focus/CHEMUK-Highlights-from-2023?src=content-embed"><img src="https://www.news-medical.net/images/pdf-dl-cta.png" alt="" width="74" height="74" /></a>CHEMUK - Highlights from 2023 eBook&nbsp;Compilation of the top interviews, articles, and news in the last year.<a href="https://www.news-medical.net/industry-focus/CHEMUK-Highlights-from-2023?src=content-embed">Download the latest edition</a></div></div></div><p>The dietary intervention provided CRHP meals comprising 30% of energy (E%) from carbohydrates, 30 E% from protein, and 40 E% from fat, compared to 50 E%, 17 E%, and 33 E% in the CD diet.</p><p>All meals were prepared and distributed by research staff to ensure adherence, with participants instructed to consume only the provided foods. Weight maintenance or loss was managed according to the study design, with physical activity maintained at habitual levels.</p><p>Blood samples and lipoprotein profiling were performed pre- and post-intervention, analyzing parameters such as HbA1c, lipid concentrations, and insulin resistance. Intrahepatic triglyceride (IHTG) content was assessed via magnetic resonance spectroscopy.</p><p>Statistical analyses, including linear mixed models, evaluated diet effects and accounted for body weight fluctuations. Correlations between changes in IHTG and lipid profiles were assessed using Pearson&rsquo;s analysis.</p><h2>Study results</h2><p>In both studies, participant retention was high, with only 7% withdrawing after randomization for reasons unrelated to trial outcomes or adverse events. The baseline characteristics of participants in the Iso and Hypo studies were generally comparable.</p><p>However, participants in the Hypo study were more obese, had higher fasting insulin concentrations, and were more insulin resistant than those in the Iso study. In the Hypo study, baseline characteristics between dietary groups were balanced except for a higher proportion of men and participants using dipeptidyl peptidase-4 (DPP-4) inhibitors in the CRHP group.</p><p>Most participants had well-managed dyslipidemia, with group mean concentrations of TAG, LDL cholesterol, and HDL cholesterol within normal ranges.</p><p>In the Iso study, body weight was effectively maintained across both diet groups. However, the CRHP diet significantly improved lipoprotein profiles compared to the CD diet, reducing atherogenic subfractions of TAG-rich lipoproteins (TRL) and LDL5 while increasing the HDL2/HDL3 ratio.</p><p>These changes reflected a shift toward a less atherogenic lipoprotein profile. In the Hypo study, where both groups achieved similar weight loss, the CRHP diet showed a tendency to reduce TRL. It significantly reduced LDL5, increased the HDL2/HDL3 ratio, and demonstrated a greater improvement in IHTG compared to the CD diet.</p><p>Glucometabolic improvements were observed in both studies. In the Iso study, the CRHP diet reduced HbA1c, fasting TAG, and IHTG significantly more than the CD diet.</p><p>In the Hypo study, weight loss alone improved these markers, but the CRHP diet further enhanced the benefits, reducing HbA1c and circulating TAG more effectively than the CD diet. Both studies demonstrated superior reductions in IHTG with the CRHP diet compared to the CD diet.</p><p>Correlations between changes in IHTG and lipid parameters revealed consistent relationships. In the Iso study, reductions in IHTG were significantly associated with improvements in TAG, TRL, LDL5, and the HDL2/HDL3 ratio. Similar trends were observed in the Hypo study, where changes in IHTG correlated with reductions in TAG, TRL, and LDL5.</p><h2>Conclusions</h2><p>To summarize, the study demonstrated that a CRHP diet improved plasma lipoprotein density profiles in patients with T2D over six weeks. Key changes included reductions in fasting TAG and small-dense LDL5 particles, as well as an increased HDL2/HDL3 ratio compared to a CD diet. These effects were observed during both weight maintenance and weight loss.</p><p>Additionally, the CRHP diet lowered total cholesterol, non-HDL cholesterol, and Apolipoprotein B (ApoB) levels in the weight-maintenance setting. Improvements were strongly associated with reductions in IHTG, suggesting that liver fat depletion played a critical role.</p><p>While weight loss in both diet groups enhanced lipid profiles, the CRHP diet provided additional atheroprotective benefits, supporting its potential as a targeted dietary intervention for T2D-associated dyslipidemia and metabolic dysfunction.</p></div></div></div> ', 'https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20241205083154/ri/1750/src/images/news/ImageForNews_797479_17334055232498946.jpg', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Nutrition'), FALSE, 89, '2024-02-01 14:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Alice Johnson')),
	(UUID(), 'Can You Eat Too Much Fruit?', 'Fruit is a key source of nutrients, offering numerous health benefits. A meta-analysis of over 350 studies found that consuming at least 800g of fruits and vegetables daily significantly reduces risks of cardiovascular disease, cancer, and premature death, with benefits increasing in 200g increments. Fruit aids in weight management, lowers blood pressure, stabilizes blood glucose, and combats obesity-related conditions. Mechanisms include low caloric density, high fiber content, and phytochemicals promoting satiety and metabolic health. While excessive consumption is rarely harmful, risks from high-glycemic or processed fruits warrant further study. Increasing natural fruit intake supports better health and longevity.', '<div><div><p>Fruit has long been a recommended source of calories, fiber, and a host of nutrients. However, is there such a thing as overeating fruit?</p><div><img src="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/images/Article_Images/ImageForArticle_14459_1718253799749257.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 673px, (min-width: 1090px) 667px, (min-width: 992px) calc(66.6vw - 60px), (min-width: 480px) calc(100vw - 40px), calc(100vw - 30px)" srcset="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20240613124322/ri/2000/src/images/Article_Images/ImageForArticle_14459_1718253799749257.jpg 2000w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20240613124322/ri/1950/src/images/Article_Images/ImageForArticle_14459_1718253799749257.jpg 1950w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20240613124322/ri/1750/src/images/Article_Images/ImageForArticle_14459_1718253799749257.jpg 1750w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20240613124322/ri/1550/src/images/Article_Images/ImageForArticle_14459_1718253799749257.jpg 1550w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20240613124322/ri/1350/src/images/Article_Images/ImageForArticle_14459_1718253799749257.jpg 1350w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20240613124322/ri/1150/src/images/Article_Images/ImageForArticle_14459_1718253799749257.jpg 1150w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20240613124322/ri/950/src/images/Article_Images/ImageForArticle_14459_1718253799749257.jpg 950w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20240613124322/ri/750/src/images/Article_Images/ImageForArticle_14459_1718253799749257.jpg 750w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20240613124322/ri/550/src/images/Article_Images/ImageForArticle_14459_1718253799749257.jpg 550w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20240613124322/ri/450/src/images/Article_Images/ImageForArticle_14459_1718253799749257.jpg 450w" alt="Image Credit: VictoriaKh - Shutterstock" width="2000" height="1358" /><div><em>Image Credit: VictoriaKh - Shutterstock</em></div></div><p>A major meta-analysis examined about 350 studies performed in various parts of the world to try and pinpoint the various effects of consuming both fruits and vegetables. They looked at health outcomes, which included cardiovascular events, cancers, and early death. All the studies were prospective cohort studies, and therefore, the results proved an association between the preceding events and the outcomes but could not prove causation.</p><p>The conclusion was that the people who habitually ate 800g or more of fruit and vegetables a day &ndash; which, at ten portions, is considerably higher compared to the 5 currently recommended &ndash; lowered their risk of adverse health conditions. Cancer risk was reduced around the 600g mark. This study also tried to identify the benefits of different fruits and vegetables in various health conditions. However, this study is unlikely to translate into a current recommendation for the simple fact that most people today do not eat even the five portions that public health agencies have promoted.</p><p>This is a classic case of expediency overcoming scientific accuracy in determining what advice is given to the general population, on the plea of not wanting to put pressure on them by unrealistic goals. However, the truth is that in one study, the easily achievable intervention of physically providing food to a target group of very young adults, without any other reminders or nagging, immediately lifted the number of portions in this group by 1.2 servings a day, as well as producing significant improvements in many aspects of their mental health. This was in contrast to the lack of benefit seen in a control group who received vouchers to purchase roughly the same amount of fruits and vegetables of their own choice and to prepare them for consumption as they wished, with twice-daily reminders, even though these latter messages were not perceived as irritating but somewhat helpful. The bottom line may be that making fresh fruit available and accessible wherever people gather to eat may be the best way to increase consumption rather than endless education campaigns.</p><p>Increased fruit and vegetable consumption was analyzed by 200g increments, concerning:</p><ul><li><strong>Ischemic heart disease:</strong>&nbsp;each 200g increase in consumption reduced the risk by 8%, especially with sources of vitamin C and with apples or pears, fruit juices, green leafy vegetables, carrots, and sweet potato</li><li><strong>Stroke:</strong>&nbsp;risk reduced by 16% per 200g increase in consumption, particularly apples or pears, citrus, green leafy vegetables, and vegetable pickles</li><li><strong>Cardiovascular disease</strong>&nbsp;in general: 8% reduction per 200g increase, especially with apples or pears, citrus, carrots, green leafy vegetables, and other vegetables outside the cruciferous (Brassica) family</li><li><strong>Cancers:</strong>&nbsp;3% reduction per 200g increase, with cruciferous vegetables in particular, and with increases up to 600g per day</li><li><strong>Mortality</strong>&nbsp;from all causes together: 10% reduction per 200g increase, especially with apples or pears, citrus fruit, berries, vegetables of all kinds, and potatoes</li></ul><p>In other words, 5.6 million early deaths occurred in the year examined (2013) because these individuals ate less than 500g of fruits and vegetables daily. On the other hand, eating 800g of these daily could prevent the deaths of 7.8 million people a year.</p><p>Of course, it goes without saying that simply eating more fruits and vegetables is not a magic wand to make disease vanish. But it certainly is one of the best ways to make your food work for you and not against you, and if you also remain physically active and don&rsquo;t consume harmful things, such as smoke, alcohol, and other toxins, you are likely to live longer and more healthy than those who do.</p><p>Eating fresh fruit is even helpful in preventing diabetes mellitus as well as reducing the risk of some small-vascular complications of diabetes, such as renal disease or diabetic retinopathy, by an astonishing 28%. Apart from a 12% lesser risk of new-onset type 2 diabetes in people who regularly ate fruit,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.news-medical.net/health/What-is-Diabetes.aspx">people with diabetes</a>&nbsp;who did so had a 14% lower risk of death or secondary cardiovascular disease compared to those who ate fruit less than once a week. Apples and pears are preferred because of their low glycemic index (GI) and prolonged slow release of sugar into the blood. Bananas, grapes, and tropical fruits have a higher GI than grapes.</p><p>The global pattern is dismal, with less than 20% of people eating fruit regularly and over 6% admitting to eating it rarely or never.</p><h2>Health Benefits</h2><p>Fruit does a lot of things for the body:</p><ul><li>It reduces weight and prevents weight gain</li><li>It reduces the risk of diseases brought on by obesity, such as diabetes mellitus and heart disease, and protective effects increase as the consumption of fruit increases.</li><li>Lower blood pressure</li><li>Lower blood glucose levels</li><li>Prevents dyslipidemia</li><li>It reduces the rate of death due to all causes</li></ul><h2>How Does Fruit Reduce Body Weight?</h2><p>Many mechanisms have been suggested for the anti-obesity effect of increasing fruit consumption:</p><ul><li>Reduced caloric intake because of the low fat content and the high water and fiber content of most fruits</li><li>Producing a feeling of fullness, which reduces overall food intake and meal frequency, by the gelling of dietary fiber within the gut, and the prolonged digestion process of fruit means that satiety receptors are occupied for a longer duration.</li><li>Providing micronutrients and vitamins, which are negatively associated with weight gain by reducing gene expression in relation to fat cell production and maturation</li><li>Phytochemicals such as resveratrol, proanthocyanidins, catechins, caffeic acid, and the like are potent anti-oxidants that suppress fat cell formation and storage.</li><li>Undigested fruit fiber provides a vital substrate for gut microbiota to feed upon, to produce changes in the relative proportions of various bacterial groups, increasing the number of Bacteroides and Actinobacteria (abundant in lean people) but reducing Firmicutes and Proteobacteria, which are found in obese individuals.</li></ul><p>Acting via these numerous pathways, fruit succeeds in both reducing total energy intake and maintaining satiety. This, in turn, leads to a net lowering of fat stores (especially central) by their utilization within the body for daily energy and metabolic needs, reducing body mass. In addition, its nutrient composition favors adipocyte non-differentiation and reduces obesity.</p><p>Apples and pears are consistently associated with risk reductions in many types of disease. Notably, these contain 6% fructose and less than half that amount of sucrose. The fructose is mostly fermented within the colon because it is not well absorbed. The resulting increase in short-chain fatty acid (SCFA) production is of great value in many metabolic and physiological processes.</p><p>The few trials that support a pro-obesity effect of fruit have often failed to distinguish natural and processed fruit forms and are usually confined to a specific age group or category, in contrast to the numerous population-based trials confirming its anti-obesity activity. A single trial suggested that an overly high consumption of high-GI fruits during the second trimester led to increased rates of gestational diabetes. Still, the authors recommend further study to confirm and examine the findings. Another trial showed increased body mass with increased fruit intake at dinner time. It is yet to be confirmed that fresh fruit carries such a risk rather than preserved or juiced fruit.</p><p>In short, the net conclusion is that increasing fruit intake is rarely a health risk and carries a host of benefits &ndash; which only improve with more fruit in its natural form, whatever the glycemic load of the individual fruit.</p></div></div> ', 'https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20240613124322/ri/1750/src/images/Article_Images/ImageForArticle_14459_1718253799749257.jpg', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Nutrition'), FALSE, 89, '2024-02-01 14:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Alice Johnson')),
	(UUID(), 'The Vegan Diet, Ethos, Affects and Advice', 'Vegan diets, driven by health and environmental concerns, have gained popularity, particularly among younger people. These diets, which avoid all animal products, are associated with benefits such as lower cholesterol, blood pressure, and body weight. They also have a reduced environmental impact, with vegans having a smaller carbon footprint than meat-eaters. However, a vegan diet may lack certain essential nutrients like B-12, D, calcium, zinc, and omega-3 fatty acids, requiring careful planning or supplementation. Despite challenges in studying its long-term effects, veganism remains a viable choice for both health and sustainability.', ' <div><h1>The Vegan Diet, Ethos, Affects and Advic</h1><p>Cutting meat from one&rsquo;s diet has become increasingly popular for a number of reasons, including health and environmental concerns.</p><p>Vegan diets are characterized by the avoidance of animal products, including meat, eggs, and dairy. A vegan diet brings with it a unique set of nutritional and health considerations.</p><div><img title="Image Credit: Foxys Forest Manufacture / Shutterstock" src="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_648899398.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 673px, (min-width: 1090px) 667px, (min-width: 992px) calc(66.6vw - 60px), (min-width: 713px) 673px, (min-width: 480px) calc(100vw - 40px), calc(100vw - 30px)" srcset="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200223094543/ri/673/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_648899398.jpg 673w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200223094543/ri/650/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_648899398.jpg 650w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200223094543/ri/450/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_648899398.jpg 450w" alt="Image Credit: Foxys Forest Manufacture / Shutterstock" width="673" height="480" /><div><em>Image Credit: Foxys Forest Manufacture / Shutterstock</em></div></div><h2>The vegan ethos</h2><p>The vegan diet is particularly popular among younger people, and especially women. In 2006, 1.4% of the US population was vegan, and this increased to 3.4% by 2015.</p><p>The central idea around veganism is to avoid animal-based foods due to environmental reasons, ethical concerns regarding the treatment of farm animals, the use of chemicals such as growth stimulants in farm animals, and health advantages.</p><p>While the general plant-based contents of veganism hold true, there are several choices vegans can make, which are often influenced by their reason for becoming vegan.</p><p>The most extreme are those who eat so-called &ldquo;living food&rdquo;, which is uncooked vegan food such as seeds, vegetables, and nuts.</p><p>A large number of possible variations in what it means to be vegan can make it challenging to study how veganism impacts health.</p><p><strong>Effects of veganism</strong></p><p>Research on the effects of vegan diets has primarily focused on two areas: health and environmental impact.</p><p>Health studies show that vegan diets are associated with being thinner, having lower cholesterol, and having lower blood pressure, among other health benefits. This is primarily attributed to both food intake and modulation of the gut&nbsp;<a href="https://www.news-medical.net/health/What-is-the-Microbiome.aspx">microbiome</a>. However, long-running studies establishing the actual effectiveness of the diet and separating the effects from other factors are lacking.</p><p>Similarly, it can be challenging to assign a validated correct value to the environmental burden of meat-eating.</p><p>Several international collaborations have shown that food can be a massive emitter of greenhouse gases through production, transport, storage, cooking, and waste.</p><p>Reasons include inefficient use of land, both in terms of grazing animals and in the food used to feed livestock and methane released by livestock.</p><div><img title="Beef cattle. Image Credit: Critterbiz / Shutterstock" src="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_386294152.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 673px, (min-width: 1090px) 667px, (min-width: 992px) calc(66.6vw - 60px), (min-width: 713px) 673px, (min-width: 480px) calc(100vw - 40px), calc(100vw - 30px)" srcset="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200223095212/ri/673/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_386294152.jpg 673w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200223095212/ri/650/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_386294152.jpg 650w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200223095212/ri/450/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_386294152.jpg 450w" alt="Beef cattle. Image Credit: Critterbiz / Shutterstock" width="673" height="460" /><div><em>Beef cattle. Image Credit: Critterbiz / Shutterstock</em></div></div><p>Studies that have compared meat eaters to vegans and vegetarians have estimated that meat-eaters have a carbon footprint that is more than double the footprint of vegans.</p><p>Specifically, meat-eaters are estimated to have greenhouse gas emissions of 7.19 kgCO<sub>2</sub>e/day compared to 2.89 kgCO<sub>2</sub>e/day for vegans. Therefore, there is some support that vegan diets can be effective for individuals who change their diet for environmental reasons.</p><p><strong>Recommendations for vegans</strong></p><p>Because a lot of commonly consumed nutrients from meat and dairy are omitted from a vegan diet, there are some dietary recommendations for vegans that are generally made. These can be in the form of natural sources, fortified foods, or through pill supplements.</p><p>Among vitamins, B-12 and D are advised to be supplemented. Foods can be fortified with B-12 to allow vegans to consume B-12 as part of their regular diet, in foods such as fortified soy beverages and nutritional yeast. Vitamin B-12 can also naturally be found in some breakfast cereals. Vitamin D can be found in drinks such as orange juice.</p><p>Other essential nutrients that usually need to be supplemented in a vegan diet are calcium and zinc. While calcium is common in many staple vegan foods such as leafy green vegetables and tofu, it usually needs to be complemented with calcium-fortified foods such as fruit juices.</p><p>Zinc is also common in many vegan staples, such as grains and legumes, but vegans should be careful to consume enough of these to balance out the high phytate content of a classic vegan diet.</p><p>Healthy fatty acids, such as omega-3, is common in fish, and thus often missed out on in vegan diets.</p><p>Vegans are recommended to eat foods rich in n-3 fatty acid ALA, such as walnuts and soy products, and n-3 fatty acid DHA, such as soy milk and cereal bars. This is especially important for pregnant and lactating women, who may wish to use additional supplements of long-chain n-3 fatty acids.</p></div> ', 'https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200223094543/ri/673/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_648899398.jpg', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Technology'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Bob Smith')),
	(UUID(), 'What are the Health Benefits of a Vegan Diet?', 'Adopting a vegan diet is linked to various health benefits, including weight management, lower cholesterol, and reduced blood pressure. Vegan diets, typically high in fiber, vitamins, and antioxidants, can improve metabolism and cardiovascular health, while potentially lowering cancer risks due to the increased consumption of fruits and vegetables. However, vegans may face nutrient deficiencies, such as low vitamin B-12 and D, which could affect cognitive health. Despite these concerns, the overall health benefits of a vegan diet suggest it may promote longevity and prevent certain chronic diseases.', ' <div><p>While there are a variety of reasons for adopting a vegan diet, health reasons are attracting a lot of scientific focus. Vegans tend to be thinner, have lower cholesterol, and have lower blood pressure, and there is some evidence there are additional health benefits that can lead to longer life expectancy.</p><div><img title="Vegan burger. Image Credit: Magdanatka / Shutterstock" src="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_1078632029.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 673px, (min-width: 1090px) 667px, (min-width: 992px) calc(66.6vw - 60px), (min-width: 713px) 673px, (min-width: 480px) calc(100vw - 40px), calc(100vw - 30px)" srcset="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200218101919/ri/673/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_1078632029.jpg 673w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200218101919/ri/650/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_1078632029.jpg 650w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200218101919/ri/450/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_1078632029.jpg 450w" alt="Vegan burger. Image Credit: Magdanatka / Shutterstock" width="673" height="449" /><div><em>Vegan burger. Image Credit: Magdanatka / Shutterstock</em></div></div><h2>Metabolism benefits</h2><p>Vegans benefit from increased consumption of vegetables but can miss out on essential nutrients due to the avoidance of meat and dairy. Vegan diets are usually high in fiber, magnesium, folic acid, phytochemicals, and vitamins C and E. On the other hand, they tend to be lower in calories, saturated fat, cholesterol, omega 3 fatty acids, calcium, zinc, and vitamins B-12 and D.</p><p>Studies in the short and moderate-term have found that vegan diets can improve energy metabolism in healthy, obese, and type 2 diabetic individuals. Some believe this is due to favorable changes in the gut&nbsp;<a href="https://www.news-medical.net/health/What-is-the-Microbiome.aspx">microbiome</a>&nbsp;that are brought about due to the vegan diet, but there is currently not enough research to verify this. There is also some evidence that vegans consume more protective nutrients and phytochemicals.</p><p><strong>Cardiovascular benefits</strong></p><p>Diets that are high in fruits and vegetables, nuts, vegetable oils, and whole grain are often associated with lower rates of cardiovascular disease development. These types of diets traditionally include Mediterranean and Asian diets, but recently the vegan diet has been postulated to have similar effects.</p><p>The lower risk of cardiovascular disease can be achieved by a vegetarian diet, where dairy is included. This seems to be primarily due to the increased intake of fruits and vegetables, which contain valuable nutrients, including fiber and antioxidant vitamins, and have been independently associated with a lower risk of cardiovascular disease.</p><div><img title="Berries rich with antioxidants. Image Credit: Leonori / Shutterstock" src="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_311981927.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 673px, (min-width: 1090px) 667px, (min-width: 992px) calc(66.6vw - 60px), (min-width: 713px) 673px, (min-width: 480px) calc(100vw - 40px), calc(100vw - 30px)" srcset="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200218102726/ri/673/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_311981927.jpg 673w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200218102726/ri/650/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_311981927.jpg 650w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200218102726/ri/450/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_311981927.jpg 450w" alt="Berries rich with antioxidants. Image Credit: Leonori / Shutterstock" width="673" height="450" /><div><em>Berries rich with antioxidants. Image Credit: Leonori / Shutterstock</em></div></div><p>While vegan diets are often seen as having lower fat content and vegans are usually thinner, the actual benefits of fat intake associated with veganism on cardiovascular diseases are disputed. In general, vegetable oils are seen as more beneficial than animal fat due to their content of monounsaturated fats, vitamin E, and &alpha;-linolenic acid.</p><p><strong>Effects on cancer prevalence</strong></p><p>A lot of evidence indicates that vegans and vegetarians have a lower risk of various cancers, both due directly to nutrient intake and due to secondary effects. For example, obesity is a significant factor in cancer risk, and due to the lower BMI of vegans, they also enjoy lower cancer risk.</p><div data-event-label="eBook: Hallmarks of Neurodegeneration, Rel: Secondary, Loc: Content. Comp: 18 items" data-event-logged="true">&nbsp;</div><p>Fruits and vegetables have been described as lowering the risk of lung, mouth, esophagus, and stomach cancers, and they tend to be consumed at higher quantities in vegans. Phytochemicals, which are abundant in vegetables and occur at a higher volume in vegan diets, have antioxidant qualities and disrupt cells to stop the progression of cancer.</p><p>While vegan diets include nutrients known to lower the risk of cancer, there can also be adverse effects of vegan diets on cancer risks. For example, low vitamin D is associated with increased cancer risk and is also generally low in vegan diets. This may explain why there are not more pronounced differences in the development of cancer between vegans and non-vegans. Vegans may have increased risks due to deficiencies but decreased risks due to increased antioxidant consumption or lower body weight.</p><p><strong>Cognitive benefits</strong></p><p>One of the lesser-studied areas in how vegan diets can affect an individual is neurobiology and cognitive function. Studies that have focused on this have found mild or moderate improvements when patients afflicted with migraine, multiple sclerosis, fibromyalgia, and rheumatoid arthritis consumed a vegan diet. These studies are confounded by not accounting for the gluten content of the plant-based diet and by small sample sizes.</p><p>Studies looking at specific nutrients show some signs that vegan diets can be beneficial for cognition and mental health. Intake of phytochemicals, which appears to be higher in vegans, is associated with beneficial effects on mental health. In contrast, lower intake of vitamin B-12, which is common in vegans, is associated with detrimental effects on the neurologic system and cognitive health, such as stroke, Parkinson&rsquo;s disease, and Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease.</p></div>', 'https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20200218101919/ri/673/picture/2020/2/%40shutterstock_1078632029.jpg', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Programming'), FALSE, 89, '2024-02-01 14:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Alice Johnson')),
	(UUID(), 'Mental Health as a Universal Human Right: NAMI Mission on World Mental Health Day', 'NAMI mission to promote mental health as a universal human right aligns with the theme of World Mental Health Day 2023. Through advocacy, education, and support, NAMI works to combat stigma, improve access to mental health care, and ensure dignity and equity for individuals with mental health conditions. The organization offers resources such as peer-led support groups, the NAMI HelpLine, and educational programs while advocating for policy changes like crisis response system reforms and better mental health care parity. By fostering open discussions and policy advancements, NAMI strives to make mental health care accessible to all, emphasizing the importance of mental health as a fundamental human right.', ' <div><h2>Can you please introduce yourself and tell us about your role at NAMI? How did you get involved in mental health advocacy?</h2><p>My name is Matt Raymond and I have been director of communications at NAMI since July 2021. As part of the marketing and communications team, we are always looking for strategic and innovative ways to communicate about mental health by telling purpose-driven, authentic and impactful stories.<br /><br />Similar to so many of us at NAMI, I have what we call &ldquo;lived experience&rdquo; with mental health conditions and mental illness, both personally and also with many of my family members and friends. As a member of the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/Blogs/NAMI-Blog/June-2023/I-Think-I-Might-Be-Gay" rel="noopener">LGBTQ+ community</a>, and with family members who are also part of that community, I have actively worked for decades to promote many of the same goals that NAMI has advanced since its founding in 1979.<br /><br />While I had some familiarity with NAMI prior to working here, I came across the job opening by chance. I feel so fortunate to work at a place that has such dedicated people with a strong sense of mission, and a humble appreciation for the real difference we can make in people&rsquo;s lives.</p><h2>NAMI has been doing significant work in the field of mental health. Could you share some key initiatives or programs that NAMI has undertaken to promote mental health awareness and support?</h2><p>Some examples of our work include our advocacy for a better&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/988" rel="noopener">crisis response</a>&nbsp;system (discussed in more detail below),&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/Get-Involved/Awareness-Events" rel="noopener">awareness</a>&nbsp;initiatives and campaigns, the NAMI&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/help" rel="noopener">HelpLine</a>, peer-led&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/supportgroups" rel="noopener">support groups</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/Support-Education/Mental-Health-Education" rel="noopener">education programs</a>, resources for broad and diverse&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/Your-Journey/" rel="noopener">populations</a>, and&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/Support-Education/Publications-Reports/Survey-Reports" rel="noopener">primary research</a>.</p><div data-video-url="https://www.youtube.com/embed/BZNw3Ldtxrg?si=fRFnXhZ4dLswLU-n&amp;enablejsapi=1" data-orig-embed-width="560" data-orig-embed-height="315">Welcome To NAMI</div><h2>World Mental Health Day is approaching, and the theme for 2023 is "Mental health is a universal human right." What does this theme mean to NAMI, and how does it align with your organizations mission?</h2><p>NAMI envisions a world where all people affected by mental illness live healthy, fulfilling lives supported by a community that cares. We work to achieve this mission through advocacy, education, support and public awareness so that all individuals and families affected by mental illness can build better lives.<br /><br />On World Mental Health Day, we are reminded of the importance of advocacy, so that all people with mental illness are treated with dignity, respect and equity.</p><p><img src="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968679613045093.png" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 673px, (min-width: 1090px) 667px, (min-width: 992px) calc(66.6vw - 60px), (min-width: 480px) calc(100vw - 40px), calc(100vw - 30px)" srcset="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121242/ri/1902/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968679613045093.png 1902w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121242/ri/1850/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968679613045093.png 1850w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121242/ri/1650/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968679613045093.png 1650w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121242/ri/1450/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968679613045093.png 1450w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121242/ri/1250/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968679613045093.png 1250w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121242/ri/1050/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968679613045093.png 1050w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121242/ri/850/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968679613045093.png 850w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121242/ri/650/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968679613045093.png 650w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121242/ri/450/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968679613045093.png 450w" alt="" width="1902" height="742" /></p><h2>In what ways does NAMI contribute to raising awareness about mental health as a fundamental human right, not just on World Mental Health Day but throughout the year?</h2><p>NAMI continually works to elevate the conversation around mental health in many ways, including educational programs, community outreach, advocacy campaigns, events, social media, news media, and other public outreach. Our aim is to normalize discussions about mental health and make early support and treatment more accessible to everyone. Through our work, we want to empower people to seek help and communities to offer better support systems.</p><h2>The COVID-19 pandemic has had a significant impact on mental health worldwide. How has NAMI adapted its work to address the mental health challenges exacerbated by the pandemic?</h2><p>NAMI continues to fight stigma and discrimination, particularly for communities disproportionately affected by the pandemic. We have strongly supported legislation, policies and funding to address our underfunded, fractured mental health system to help address a mental health epidemic within the pandemic.<br /><br />We have also developed&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/Support-Education/NAMI-HelpLine/COVID-19-Information-and-Resources/COVID-19-Resource-and-Information-Guide" rel="noopener">COVID resources</a>&nbsp;to address the mental health challenges exacerbated by the pandemic, offering credible information and resources on managing anxiety, accessing medication during quarantine and coping with the loss of a loved one. Our NAMI&nbsp;<a href="https://nami.org/help" rel="noopener">HelpLine</a>&nbsp;quickly pivoted when the pandemic began, using new technology and systems to continue offer support and resources to those seeking help, and NAMI affiliates across the nation have online support groups.</p><h2>Mental health stigma remains a barrier to accessing care and support. How is NAMI working to combat stigma and promote a more accepting and understanding society?</h2><p>Millions of people in the U.S. are affected by mental illness each year, yet less than half are able to receive treatment. NAMI actively works to reduce barriers to care and combat mental health stigma through educational campaigns and awareness-raising initiatives.<br /><br />We aim to create an environment where mental health is openly discussed so that we can increase access to care and support. We fight for public policy changes to that all people with mental health conditions have accessible, affordable and comprehensive health care.</p><h2>NAMI often advocates for policy changes related to mental health. Can you share some recent policy successes or ongoing initiatives aimed at improving mental health services and access in the United States?</h2><p>Last year, policy makers at the federal level dedicated an unprecedented amount of funding to a variety of NAMI&rsquo;s mental health priorities. This included significant funding for the national 988 Suicide and Crisis Lifeline (&ldquo;988&rdquo;), crisis response services, the Community Mental Health Block Grant, suicide prevention programs, research, and criminal justice diversion programs.<br /><br />Additionally, among many other&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/Advocacy/" rel="noopener">efforts</a>, NAMI has led a broad partnership called&nbsp;<a href="https://reimaginecrisis.org/" rel="noopener">Reimagine Crisis Response</a>&nbsp;that brings together a diverse group of leading organizations to reimagine our national response to people experiencing a mental health, suicide or substance use crisis. Another major, ongoing focus has been to increase enforcement of mental health care parity, so that our nation&rsquo;s health care system will treat mental health coverage just as it does for our physical health.<br /><br />NAMI takes a variety of&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/Advocacy/NAMI-Advocacy-Actions" rel="noopener">actions</a>&nbsp;to advance our public policy agenda and regularly publishes&nbsp;<a href="https://nami.org/Support-Education/Publications-Reports/Public-Policy-Reports" rel="noopener">reports</a>&nbsp;to help inform the public about the importance of effective mental health policy.</p><p><img src="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968681608719668.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 673px, (min-width: 1090px) 667px, (min-width: 992px) calc(66.6vw - 60px), (min-width: 480px) calc(100vw - 40px), calc(100vw - 30px)" srcset="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121602/ri/2000/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968681608719668.jpg 2000w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121602/ri/1950/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968681608719668.jpg 1950w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121602/ri/1750/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968681608719668.jpg 1750w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121602/ri/1550/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968681608719668.jpg 1550w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121602/ri/1350/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968681608719668.jpg 1350w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121602/ri/1150/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968681608719668.jpg 1150w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121602/ri/950/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968681608719668.jpg 950w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121602/ri/750/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968681608719668.jpg 750w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121602/ri/550/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968681608719668.jpg 550w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121602/ri/450/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968681608719668.jpg 450w" alt="" width="2000" height="1333" /><em>Image Credit:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.shutterstock.com/g/DraganaGordic" rel="noopener">Dragana Gordic</a>/Shutterstock.com</em></p><h2>NAMI provides support to individuals and families affected by mental illness. Can you talk about some of the resources and support services available through NAMI that people can access?</h2><p>In addition to some of the programs and initiatives discussed above, NAMI offers a variety of resources, including a HelpLine that operates on weekdays. We also provide specialized services like the Teen &amp; Young Adult HelpLine and a Resource Directory, offering comprehensive support and information to different age groups and communities.</p><p>NAMI support groups, made available nationwide through about 750 state organizations and affiliates, offer participants an opportunity to share their experiences and gain support from others who understand what they&rsquo;re going through.</p><h2>What can individuals, communities, and policymakers do to ensure that mental health truly becomes a universal human right, as emphasized in the theme for World Mental Health Day 2023?</h2><p>To make mental health more accessible and effective, people can advocate for policy changes and support organizations like NAMI. Communities can foster open dialogues about mental health to combat stigma. And policymakers can prioritize mental health and allocate sufficient resources for mental health services and systems.</p><h2>Looking forward, what are NAMIs goals and priorities in the coming year to further advance the cause of mental health awareness and support?</h2><p>NAMI&rsquo;s top priorities include leading the mental health movement to improve access to care and crisis response; expanding reach and impact among youth, young adults, workplaces and minoritized communities; and using innovation and research to reach people with education, support, and improving access to effective and timely care.</p><h2>How can individuals and organizations get involved with NAMIs efforts or support its mission in promoting mental health as a universal human right?</h2><p>&nbsp;Individuals and organizations can&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/Get-Involved" rel="noopener">get involved</a>&nbsp;with NAMI by:</p><ul><li><a href="https://nami.applicantpro.com/jobs/2561057.html" rel="noopener">Volunteering</a>&nbsp;for our HelpLine</li><li><a href="https://donate.nami.org/give/509521/#!/donation/checkout?eg=true&amp;c_src=EMBD23" rel="noopener">Donating</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/Get-Involved/Become-a-Fundraiser" rel="noopener">raising</a>&nbsp;funds</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/advocacy" rel="noopener">Participating</a>&nbsp;in advocacy actions</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/Get-Involved/Awareness-Events" rel="noopener">Taking part</a>&nbsp;in awareness campaigns</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/findsupport" rel="noopener">Getting involved</a>&nbsp;with a local NAMI or support group</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/About-Mental-Illness" rel="noopener">Learning</a>&nbsp;about mental illness, as well as NAMI&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/Your-Journey" rel="noopener">programs</a>&nbsp;and initiatives</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/Get-Involved/Pledge-to-Be-StigmaFree/StigmaFree-Company" rel="noopener">Becoming</a>&nbsp;a StigmaFree company</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/About-NAMI/Form-a-NAMI-Affiliate" rel="noopener">Forming</a>&nbsp;an affiliate</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/About-NAMI/Who-We-Are/Meet-Our-Partners" rel="noopener">Becoming</a>&nbsp;a partner</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/Get-Involved/Share-Your-Story" rel="noopener">Sharing</a>&nbsp;your story</li><li>Attending events like&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nami.org/Get-Involved/Find-a-NAMIWalk" rel="noopener">NAMIWalks</a>&nbsp;and our annual&nbsp;<a href="https://convention.nami.org/" rel="noopener">NAMICon</a>&nbsp;convention</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/About-NAMI/Work-at-NAMI" rel="noopener">Applying</a>&nbsp;for jobs</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/Get-Involved/NAMI-On-Campus" rel="noopener">Starting</a>&nbsp;a NAMI On Campus club</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/Get-Involved/NAMI-FaithNet" rel="noopener">Getting involved</a>&nbsp;in NAMI FaithNet</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/Support-Education/Publications-Reports/You-Are-Not-Alone" rel="noopener">Buying</a>&nbsp;NAMI&rsquo;s first book, &ldquo;You Are Not Alone&rdquo;</li><li><a href="https://nami.org/podcast" rel="noopener">Listening</a>&nbsp;to our podcasts and webinars</li><li><a href="https://www.nami.org/Support-Education/Publications-Reports" rel="noopener">Subscribing</a>&nbsp;to our newsletters and publications</li><li>And following us on&nbsp;<a href="https://www.facebook.com/NAMI" rel="noopener">Facebook</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://twitter.com/namicommunicate" rel="noopener">X</a>&nbsp;(formerly Twitter),&nbsp;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/NAMIvideo" rel="noopener">YouTube</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.instagram.com/NAMICommunicate/" rel="noopener">Instagram</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/nami/" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.tiktok.com/@nami" rel="noopener">TikTok</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://www.threads.net/@namicommunicate" rel="noopener">Threads</a></li></ul></div> ', 'https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20231009121242/ri/1650/src/images/news/ImageForNews_761155_16968679613045093.png', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Mental Health'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Charlie Davis')),
	(UUID(), 'Integrated mental health care improves children mental health and school performance', 'A recent study led by Boston Medical Center and Boston University School of Public Health reveals that integrated mental health care significantly improves children mental health and school performance. Published in the Journal of Developmental & Behavioral Pediatrics, the research followed 51 children aged 6-12 who received integrated behavioral health care through the TEAM UP Model at three federally qualified health centers (FQHCs) in Massachusetts. Over 12 months, the children showed substantial improvements in mental health symptoms, health-related quality of life, and school-related functional outcomes. TEAM UP, designed to integrate trauma-responsive, evidence-informed behavioral health care into pediatric care for marginalized communities, addresses significant unmet mental health needs in these populations. The study highlights the potential of integrated care to positively impact both mental health and school attendance, encouraging more FQHCs to adopt this model.', '<div><p>New research led by Boston Medical Center and Boston University School of Public Health found that children who received integrated mental health care showed improvements in both mental health and school performance. These findings, published in the&nbsp;<em>Journal of Developmental &amp; Behavioral Pediatrics,</em>&nbsp;examined changes over time in outcomes among 6-12-year-old children receiving integrated behavioral health care at three federally qualified health centers (FQHCs) that implemented the TEAM UP Model of care.</p><p>The study, which included 51 children serviced by FQHCs in Massachusetts, found that over 12 months of receiving integrated mental health care, childrens mental health symptoms, health-related quality of life, and school-related functional outcomes significantly improved, supporting the potential benefits of pediatric integrated behavioral health care.</p><p>TEAM UP for Children-;Transforming and Expanding Access to Mental Health Care in Urban Pediatrics-; is a pediatric integrated behavioral health initiative co-developed by Boston Medical Center and seven FQHCs designed to equip health centers to deliver high-quality, evidence-informed, trauma-responsive, integrated behavioral healthcare in historically marginalized communities. In these health centers, where 74% of the patient population is from a racial and/or ethnic minoritized group, 37% are best served in a language other than English, and 67% live at or below the federal poverty level, TEAM UP has created a sustainable, adaptable, and replicable model that strengthens pediatric primary care.</p><blockquote><p>Unmet service needs are significant for children experiencing mental health problems, especially for children from historically marginalized communities and those from low-income families. The TEAM UP Model aims to address this challenge by fully integrating behavioral health care into primary care at FQHCs, where children from historically marginalized communities regularly access care."</p><p>Dr. Chris Sheldrick</p></blockquote><p>The research fills a gap in the existing evidence of the relationship between mental health symptoms and school-related functioning. The study found that improvements in internalizing symptoms and mental health-related quality-of-life were associated with improvements in school attendance, suggesting that changes in mental health could positively impact school functioning.</p><p>"Integrated behavioral health care implemented in FQHCs which serve minoritized populations - as demonstrated by the TEAM UP model - shows promise in enhancing overall child well-being," said Dr. Jihye Kim, Visiting Assistant Professor at the University of Nevada, Las Vegas, and a researcher for TEAM UP.</p><div data-event-label="Industry Focus: Infectious Diseases, Rel: Secondary, Loc: Content. Comp: 9 items" data-event-logged="true"><div><div>The researchers hope their findings will encourage more FQHCs to integrate behavioral health services into their pediatric primary care practices.</div></div></div><p>According to co-author Megan Bair-Merritt, MD, MSCE, Chief Scientific Officer at Boston Medical Center, "In the wake of the COVID-19 pandemic, children across the country have struggled with mental health challenges. These results are promising in suggesting the potentially positive impact of behavioral integration on childrens mental health, health-related quality of life, and school-related functioning."</p></div> ', 'https://epe.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/03f0e5e/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1695x1150+13+0/resize/840x570!/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fepe-brightspot.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F9c%2Fe57d38984e6f8a2b98b6d1083781%2Flead-art-1.jpg', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Mental Health'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Charlie Davis')),
	(UUID(), 'World Mental Health Day 2022: Mental Health for All', 'World Mental Health Day 2022 focused on raising awareness around mental health, highlighting the need for a global commitment to mental wellbeing. Professor Charlotte Hanlon, a psychiatrist with extensive experience in global mental health, emphasizes the importance of expanding mental health care, especially in low- and middle-income countries. With over 15 years of work in Ethiopia, she discusses the challenges of mental health, including the treatment gap and the effects of the COVID-19 pandemic. Through her leadership at the Centre for Global Mental Health, Professor Hanlon advocates for a multi-sectoral approach to address mental health issues, prioritizing the voices of those with lived experiences.', ' <div><h2>Please can you introduce yourself and tell us about your background in psychiatry and mental health research?</h2><p>I trained as a psychiatrist in the UK, and then I came to Ethiopia to do my Ph.D., which involved looking at the epidemiology and the impacts of perinatal depression on women and their children. Ive lived and worked in Ethiopia for 15 years. My work has shifted direction, and now Im more focused on expanding access to care for people with mental health conditions. That tends to involve the co-development,&nbsp;testing, and&nbsp;implementation of different sorts of psychological interventions, service models, and health systems strengthening approaches.&nbsp;</p><p><img src="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653895880931492.png" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 673px, (min-width: 1090px) 667px, (min-width: 992px) calc(66.6vw - 60px), (min-width: 991px) 951px, (min-width: 480px) calc(100vw - 40px), calc(100vw - 30px)" srcset="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20221010041306/ri/951/src/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653895880931492.png 951w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20221010041306/ri/950/src/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653895880931492.png 950w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20221010041306/ri/750/src/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653895880931492.png 750w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20221010041306/ri/550/src/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653895880931492.png 550w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20221010041306/ri/450/src/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653895880931492.png 450w" alt="" width="951" height="371" /></p><h2>Earlier this year, you were appointed as one of the new directors of the Centre for Global Mental Health. Could you tell us about the centers mission, vision, and approach?</h2><p>Im one of three directors with Professor Crick Lund and Dr. Ritsuko Kakuma. The center started in 2009 and was very much focused on addressing inequities experienced by people with mental health conditions around the world, particularly focusing on low and middle-income countries. That remains still at the heart of the centers mission and vision.</p><p>The focus of the Centre is to enable people with lived experience of mental health conditions to attain the highest possible level of health and to participate fully in society and at work, free from stigmatization and discrimination. So very much focused on putting people with lived experience at the center.</p><p>There are three strands to what the center does. Theres the research strand around producing contextually relevant evidence that can be relevant for local settings but also have a global impact. Secondly, to strengthen&nbsp;capacity when we work with partners in low and middle-income countries and to work to establish equitable partnerships. Thirdly, to work across stakeholder groups. So to engage not just in the research community but also involve people with lived experience,&nbsp;policymakers, and other stakeholders.</p><p>Perhaps one of the distinctive things that marks out our center compared to others is that two directors are not based in London. Im in Ethiopia, and Crick is in South Africa. We very much see that as part of the first step in recognizing that the center is a distributed center across our many partners and collaborations around the globe. The focus that we have is on shifting that center of gravity to our low and middle-income country partners because we very much recognize that global mental health needs to have really strong leadership from the global south.</p><h2>You have lived and worked in Ethiopia for over 10 years. What has your work taught you about the current state of global mental health? What are the main obstacles you currently face in your work?</h2><p>Thereve been so many encouraging developments in the field, but we certainly have a long way to go. Not just in Ethiopia or Africa more broadly but also globally. The pandemic brought mental health into peoples homes and certainly increased awareness that this was a neglected problem, but that has not necessarily translated into greater commitment or funding to expand care or promote the human rights of people with mental health conditions, and those key gaps remain.</p><p>Weve managed to develop a great deal more knowledge about how to expand access to mental healthcare in culturally and contextually relevant ways. For example, the UK AID-funded PRIME&nbsp;project, the Program for Improving Mental health carE, which worked in Ethiopia and&nbsp;also four other low and middle-income countries to integrate mental health into primary care. We showed how this approach can work in practice and that it can deliver benefits as well for people with mental health conditions and their families.</p><p>Another example in Ethiopia, as part of an NIH-funded Africa focus on intervention research, we ran a randomized clinical trial that showed that mental health delivered in primary care by primary healthcare workers was both safe and effective.</p><p>Those studies really help us when were advocating; they strengthen our arguments for expanding access to care, and they also help to give implementers some kind of sense of what needs to be done. More broadly, there are some really positive changes, like more donors now supporting implementation, not just small research projects. The service user mobilization is much greater, so the voices of people with lived experience are much better represented.</p><figure><img title="Image Credit: Dragana Gordic/Shutterstock.com" src="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653883861763980.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 673px, (min-width: 1090px) 667px, (min-width: 992px) calc(66.6vw - 60px), (min-width: 480px) calc(100vw - 40px), calc(100vw - 30px)" srcset="https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20221010035314/ri/1000/src/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653883861763980.jpg 1000w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20221010035314/ri/950/src/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653883861763980.jpg 950w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20221010035314/ri/750/src/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653883861763980.jpg 750w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20221010035314/ri/550/src/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653883861763980.jpg 550w, https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20221010035314/ri/450/src/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653883861763980.jpg 450w" alt="Image Credit: Dragana Gordic/Shutterstock.com" width="1000" height="667" /><figcaption><p><em>Image Credit: Dragana Gordic/Shutterstock.com</em></p></figcaption></figure><p>Compared to 15 years ago, there are so many people working in this area now, and they come from different backgrounds, theyve got different approaches, so theres a lot more diversity and creativity in the way that we sort try to address these big problems that we have to overcome. So in that sense, theres quite a lot of momentum and a much stronger platform for change.</p><p>A key obstacle that we face in Ethiopia, which is also a factor in many other&nbsp;countries, is that mental health goes hand-in-hand with poverty. One leads to the other and sets up a vicious cycle. We cant adequately respond to the needs of people with mental health conditions just by providing treatment. We need much more of a multi-sectorial response, for example, including economic interventions. But systems are not very well set up for multi-sectional organization and coordination. It does need much stronger commitment, and I think that is probably the biggest thing we need to address now.</p><h2>Even though most people affected by mental illness live in low and middle-income countries, most mental health care resources are located in high-income countries. How does the resultant treatment gap affect individuals, and what can be done to close the gap?</h2><p>The lack of access to care and protection of human rights that somebody experiencing mental health condition may be&nbsp;exposed to can have profound effects. The key ones I would highlight are discrimination and human rights abuses, impoverishment and mortality, or premature mortality. Clearly, human rights abuses against people with mental health conditions occur around the globe. Theyre not specific to low and middle-income countries. Still, in poorly resourced settings, poorly resourced in terms of services, these violations of rights do get exacerbated by people not being able to access adequate and effective care.</p><p>For example, a person may be restrained by their family in the home because families have run out of options and dont see any alternatives. Weve done work showing that family members dont want to do this. They just see it as theyve got no other choice.</p><p>In terms of poverty, in Ethiopia, our research has shown that households that include&nbsp;a person&nbsp;whos got a severe mental health condition like schizophrenia, bipolar disorder are twice as likely to have severe food insecurity, and thats because of several factors. Partly they spend a lot of money searching for treatments that can help. Those could be traditional and religious healing settings, or it could be the scarce mental healthcare. There are the lost earnings from caregivers and the person themself. Of course, crucially, societal exclusion compounds poverty because people cannot access sort of opportunities for their livelihoods or share economic burdens within communities.</p><p>My Ethiopian colleagues have a long history of working on&nbsp;research with people with mental health conditions. They showed that, even in rural Ethiopia, a person with a severe mental health problem is at substantially higher risk of premature death. That is partly due to non-accidental death but mostly due to infectious disease and undernutrition, again reflecting the lack of access to care and discrimination.</p><p>On the more positive side, in the PRIME&nbsp;project in Ethiopia, when we expanded peoples access to mental healthcare within the primary healthcare setting, we showed that 12 months in, people were less likely to have been restrained in the home setting, that the households were substantially less likely to have food insecurity, and they reported much less discrimination.</p></div> ', 'https://d2jx2rerrg6sh3.cloudfront.net/image-handler/ts/20221010041306/ri/951/src/images/news/ImageForNews_727425_16653895880931492.png', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Mental Health'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Charlie Davis')),
	(UUID(), 'Study highlights the role of psychiatric mental health nurse practitioners in mental health care delivery', 'This study emphasizes the growing role of psychiatric mental health nurse practitioners (PMHNPs) in delivering mental health care, especially in rural areas. As the mental health crisis intensifies, exacerbated by the COVID-19 pandemic, PMHNPs have become key providers of psychiatric services, accounting for 50% of all mental health prescriber visits in rural areas where they face fewer prescribing restrictions. The research, based on Medicare claims from 2011 to 2019, reveals that while the number of PMHNPs increased by 162%, psychiatrists visits decreased by 6%. The findings highlight the essential role PMHNPs play in maintaining access to mental health care, particularly in underserved areas, and suggest that policy changes to support the PMHNP workforce could be crucial in addressing the national mental health crisis.', '<div><p>The mental health system is increasingly reliant on psychiatric mental health nurse practitioners (PMHNPs) to meet the psychiatric needs of Medicare patients, according to a new study led by researchers at Harvard T.H. Chan School of Public Health.</p><blockquote><p>We were surprised by the degree to which PMHNPs are the de facto mental health prescribers in parts of the country. In the states where PMHNPs have no restrictions on prescribing medications, these providers account for 50% of all mental health prescriber visits in rural areas, which was much greater than we had anticipated."</p><p>Michael Barnett, corresponding author, associate professor of health policy and management at Harvard Chan School</p></blockquote><p>The study will be published in the September 2022 issue of&nbsp;<em>Health Affairs</em>.</p><p>Mental health access is a public health crisis that the COVID-19 pandemic has exacerbated. While demand for mental health treatment is soaring, the supply of psychiatrists accepting insurance is dropping, particularly in rural areas.</p><p>To assess how the mental health workforce and patient population have changed over time, Barnett and his colleagues analyzed fee-for-service Medicare claims during 2011-2019. The team focused on the number of PMHNPs and psychiatrists billing Medicare, the volume of outpatient and psychiatric services by provider group, and how these numbers varied by rurality and scope-of-practice regulations, which can restrict whether a PMHNP is able to prescribe medications.</p><p>The findings showed that PMHNPs provided nearly 1 in 3 mental health prescriber visits to Medicare patients nationally by 2019. The number of PMHNPs also increased 162% during 2011-2019, while psychiatrists billing Medicare dropped by 6%. During this period, without growth in the PMHNP workforce, there would have been a decline of nearly 30% in mental health specialist visits in Medicare. Instead, the drop was 12%.</p><p>"This work puts the spotlight on PMHNPs as a critical part of the mental health workforce," said Barnett. "This is so important because we desperately need new solutions to address the current mental health crisis in this country. Policy that targets the PMHNP workforce could be a key part of the national effort to expand mental health access."</p><p>Co-author Arno Cai is also from Harvard Chan School.</p><p>This research was supported by the National Institute on Aging (K23 AG058806-01) and the National Institute of Mental Health (R01 MH112829-01) in the National Institutes of Health.</p></div> ', 'Study highlights the role of psychiatric mental health nurse practitioners in mental health care delivery', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Mental Health'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Diana Green')),
	(UUID(), 'Global Mental Health Databank launches study to understand the mental health of young people', 'The Global Mental Health Databank study, launching today, aims to enhance mental health management among young people worldwide. Focusing on youth from the United Kingdom, South Africa, and India, the project seeks to enable collaboration between young individuals and mental health researchers to better understand how to manage mental health challenges such as anxiety and depression. Led by Sage Bionetworks in partnership with Oxford University, the University of Cambridge, and other institutions, the study collects data via mobile phones and connected technologies to explore the impact of daily activities on mental health. Funded by the Wellcome Trust, the initiative will provide valuable insights into youth mental health management strategies and help researchers identify new interventions to prevent, manage, and treat anxiety and depression in young people globally.', '<div><p>Young people around the world commonly experience anxiety and depression, but it can be hard to identify how each person can best manage their own mental health.</p><p>The Global Mental Health Databank, a feasibility study officially launching today, hopes to change that by enabling youth from the United Kingdom, South Africa, and India to work directly with mental health researchers to better understand how young people can manage their mental health.</p><p>Sage Bionetworks is leading an international group of researchers from Oxford University, University of Cambridge, University of Washington, Walter Sisulu University, Higher Health, and the Centre for Mental Health Law &amp; Policy at the Indian Law Society in this effort to shift how a mental health databank could be developed and structured.</p><p>This project is funded by the mental health area team at the Wellcome Trust as a key infrastructure necessary to enable their work to identify the next generation of treatments and approaches to prevent, intervene, manage and stop relapse of anxiety and depression in young people.</p><p>This project will work directly with youth and researchers to build the blueprint for a global mental health program that directly collects data and provides insights to youth around the world. We will test how youth wish to interact with and use this system to advance their understanding of mental health.</p><p>"We are excited to create a system that supports both youth and researchers in understanding mental health management strategies," said Dr. Lara Mangravite, president of Sage Bionetworks. "We think its essential to start by developing a system that empowers young people to directly guide how their data is collected, shared and used."</p><p>Relying on mobile phones and other connected technologies, the study will collect data from youth participants about their lived experience with mental health self-management.</p><p>Collecting such data, which requires a strong partnership between youth and researchers, will provide insight into how a persons daily activities and surroundings affect their health and the success of their health-management strategies. For example, can change in sleep habits, social interactions or financial security help mitigate anxiety?</p><p>"We look forward to rich learning as to how to balance the best ways to ensure those banking their data have maximal control and privacy, with the wish to allow diverse scientists to have ready access to data to advance understanding of the active ingredients that help address youth anxiety and depression globally," said Professor Miranda Wolpert, MBE Head of the Mental Health Priority Area at Wellcome.</p><p>Leveraging existing technologies and expertise, Sage will also be testing the ability to operate a program of this nature at scale with the varied data privacy regulations of participating countries.</p><p>"India has the worlds largest population of adolescents and young people. Therefore, it is important that India is a part of such global initiatives to solve global problems affecting all of humanity, especially young people in low- and middle-income countries," said Dr. Soumitra Pathare, Director, Centre for Mental Health Law &amp; Policy, ILS, Pune, India. "We hope that Indian researchers will also find this project of value in helping them solve these mental health problems in the India context."</p><p>"This work provides an extraordinary opportunity to engage culturally and contextually diverse groups of young people and researchers on critical questions for youth mental health. This is fundamental to strengthening the science of global mental health and ensuring that the solutions are informed by specific needs," said Dr. Pamela Collins, professor of&nbsp;<a href="https://www.news-medical.net/health/What-is-Psychiatry.aspx">psychiatry</a>&nbsp;and behavioral sciences, professor of global health, and director of the UW Global Mental Health Program.</p><p>The team from the University of Washington will bring their deep experience in working with people coping with mental health challenges and how connected technologies can help assess mental health.</p><blockquote><p>Nearly every young person in the world has access to connected technologies and these technologies provide a window into their social, physical and emotional lives. By banking this data, we hope to provide the opportunity to discover which strategies do and do not help them manage their mental health."</p><p>Dr. Patricia Arean, Professor of Psychiatry and Behavioral Sciences, University of Washington School of Medicine</p></blockquote><p>The project envisions the databank as a platform that connects participants and researchers interested in studying the effects of contextual determinants, experiences, behaviors, and interventions in a real-world setting. To be successful, this platform must be technically feasible, beneficial to both data contributors and researchers, and it must operate under parameters that promote data justice.</p><p>"Data analysis should be the bedrock on which policy and practice rest, and it is therefore essential that we as researchers engage in dialogue with young people about how their data could support population mental health and ensure that their concerns about privacy and confidentiality are enshrined in governance procedures," said Tamsin Ford, Professor of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry at the University of Cambridge and Honorary Consultant at Cambridge and Peterborough NHS Foundation Trust.</p><p>"While this is still at early stages, we hope that this work will ultimately help to practically change lives globally," said Dr. Melvyn Freeman, of Higher Health. "I am personally hopeful, and quietly confident, that this databank will become the cog around which research into depression and anxiety in young people will turn in the future, and hence make a big difference to youth well-being."</p></div> ', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcReTCF9xoo75WHOC4yXBGNZq0zYjgodqYPZEw&s', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Mental Health'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Diana Green')),
	(UUID(), 'Why You Will Never Finish the Online Course You Took', 'Research shows that online course completion rates are alarmingly low, ranging from 5% to 15%. The primary culprits? Lack of structure and accountability, coupled with limited interaction and support. Without set schedules or engagement with instructors and peers, distractions and a lack of motivation often derail learners.Reflection reveals that successful course completion often depends on key features such as live mentor sessions, gamified assignments, or bite-sized video lessons. This highlights the importance of well-designed courses that foster community, interactivity, and manageable content delivery. Before investing in your next course, consider these insights and evaluate whether the course structure aligns with your learning preferences and needs.', '<div><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*abi_n-YO-WZaVb0l" alt="" width="700" height="460" /></picture></div></div><figcaption data-selectable-paragraph="">Photo by&nbsp;<a href="https://unsplash.com/@siora18?utm_source=medium&amp;utm_medium=referral" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Siora Photography</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href="https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=medium&amp;utm_medium=referral" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Unsplash</a></figcaption></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">According to research, the percentage rate for online course completion is between 5 and 15%.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">There are 2 main reasons:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>1- No Set Schedule &amp; No Accountability</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Without a set schedule and someone to hold you accountable you can easily get distracted.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>2- Limited Interaction &amp; Support</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">If there is no opportunity to meet with the instructor or the other students, you wont feel motivated to continue.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong><em>Now that you know why everybody lags, ask yourself what made you not complete that course.</em></strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">-&nbsp;<em>Was it because you lacked the motivation?</em><br />-<em>&nbsp;or Maybe the course was all video and no text or transcript? or maybe the videos were too long ( 1 hour each). They needed to be 3 min each for you to focus.</em></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Stop &amp; reflect on which course/s you finished!</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">I did.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Wow!</strong><em>&nbsp;Lightbulb.</em></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">I realized I finished courses that have:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">-&nbsp;<em>Live sessions with the mentor</em><br />-&nbsp;<em>Practical assignments with specific tasks &amp; motivational badges ( i.e. gamified)<br />or even courses where the 60-minute video is split into 12 videos of 5 min each.</em></p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Now I think twice before buying an online course.</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">If theres no community or no interaction, the recorded sessions are not worth it + you can find anything you want on YouTube.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">P.S: ( Another AHA)<br /><em>I found out that course creators usually put the most meat on YouTube.<br />Then they sell you a course with similar stuff, but additional &ldquo; fine-tuned&rdquo; details.</em></p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>This might work for now, but in the long run, consumers will catch up with this, and change their behaviour.</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">What do you think?</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><em>Have you reflected on your buying behaviour, especially when it comes to online learning? &amp; what have you found out?</em></p></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*abi_n-YO-WZaVb0l', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Online Courses'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Eve Wilson')),
	(UUID(), 'NVIDIA just released FREE online courses in AI. Here are 9 courses you can''t afford to miss!', 'NVIDIA has launched a series of free online AI courses, offering valuable insights into topics like Generative AI, neural networks, large-scale image classification, and Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG). These courses cover practical applications, GPU-accelerated data science workflows, and scalable AI deployment strategies. With accessible learning materials for both beginners and advanced learners, this initiative empowers individuals to deepen their understanding of cutting-edge AI technologies. Don''t miss this chance to explore NVIDIA''s transformative educational resources and accelerate your AI expertise.', '<h1 data-testid="storyTitle" data-selectable-paragraph="">NVIDIA just released FREE online courses in AI. Here are 9 courses you can&rsquo;t afford to miss!&nbsp;</h1><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 1400w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-testid="og" /><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM" alt="" width="700" height="466" /></picture></div></div><figcaption data-selectable-paragraph="">Photo by&nbsp;<a href="https://unsplash.com/@glenncarstenspeters?utm_source=medium&amp;utm_medium=referral" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Glenn Carstens-Peters</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href="https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=medium&amp;utm_medium=referral" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Unsplash</a></figcaption></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>1. Generative AI Explained</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">What you&rsquo;ll learn:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Generative AI and explain how Generative AI works.<br />Various Generative AI applications.<br />Challenges and opportunities in Generative AI</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Link :&nbsp;<a href="https://courses.nvidia.com/courses/course-v1:DLI+S-FX-07+V1/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">https://courses.nvidia.com/courses/course-v1:DLI+S-FX-07+V1/</a></p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>2. Building A Brain in 10 Minutes</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">What you&rsquo;ll learn:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Exploring how neural networks use data to learn<br />Understanding the math behind a neuron</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Link :&nbsp;<a href="https://courses.nvidia.com/courses/course-v1:DLI+T-FX-01+V1/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">https://courses.nvidia.com/courses/course-v1:DLI+T-FX-01+V1/</a></p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>3. Augment your LLM with Retrieval Augmented Generation</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">What you&rsquo;ll learn:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Basics of Retrieval Augmented Generation<br />RAG retrieval process<br />NVIDIA AI Foundations and RAG model components</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Link :&nbsp;<a href="https://courses.nvidia.com/courses/course-v1:NVIDIA+S-FX-16+v1/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">https://courses.nvidia.com/courses/course-v1:NVIDIA+S-FX-16+v1/</a></p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>4. AI in the Data Center</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">What you&rsquo;ll learn:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">AI use cases, Machine Learning, Deep Learning, and their workflows.<br />GPU architecture and its impact on AI.<br />Deep learning frameworks, and deployment considerations.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Link :&nbsp;<a href="https://www.coursera.org/learn/introduction-ai-data-center" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">https://www.coursera.org/learn/introduction-ai-data-center</a></p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>5. Accelerate Data Science Workflows with Zero Code Changes</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">What you&rsquo;ll learn:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Learn benefits of unified CPU and GPU workflows.<br />GPU-accelerate data processing and ML without code changes.<br />Experience faster processing times</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Link :&nbsp;<a href="https://courses.nvidia.com/courses/course-v1:DLI+T-DS-03+V1/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">https://courses.nvidia.com/courses/course-v1:DLI+T-DS-03+V1/</a></p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>6. Networking Introduction</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">What you&rsquo;ll learn:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Learn about networks and their importance.<br />Explore Ethernet basics and data forwarding in Ethernet networks.<br />Discuss network components, requirements, OSI model, TCP/IP protocol</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Link :&nbsp;<a href="https://www.coursera.org/learn/introduction-to-networking-nvidia" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">https://www.coursera.org/learn/introduction-to-networking-nvidia</a></p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>7. How to Perform Large-Scale Image Classification</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">What you&rsquo;ll learn:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Learn large-scale image classification.<br />Cover challenges, modelling techniques AND validation strategies.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Link :&nbsp;<a href="https://www.classcentral.com/course/youtube-grandmaster-series-how-to-perform-large-scale-image-classification-130184" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">https://www.classcentral.com/course/youtube-grandmaster-series-how-to-perform-large-scale-image-classification-130184</a></p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>8. Building RAG Agents with LLMs</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">What you&rsquo;ll learn:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Scalable deployment strategies for LLMs and vector databases.<br />Modern LangChain paradigms for dialog management and document retrieval.<br />Using advanced models and steps for production.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Link :&nbsp;<a href="https://courses.nvidia.com/courses/course-v1:DLI+S-FX-15+V1/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">https://courses.nvidia.com/courses/course-v1:DLI+S-FX-15+V1/</a></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">That&rsquo;s a wrap for this article, follow me if you want to keep enjoying such articles daily!</p><blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph="">If you want Advance ChatGPT Prompts to finish your hours of work in minutes then, Click&nbsp;<a href="https://yourdigitalagency.gumroad.com/l/ChatGPT-Prompts-Handbook" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><strong>HERE</strong></a>.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">If you want to learn Prompt Engineering, You can learn it from&nbsp;<a href="https://yourdigitalagency.gumroad.com/l/Ultimate-Prompt-Engineering-Guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><strong>HERE</strong></a>.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><a href="https://evolving-worlds-ai-newsletter.beehiiv.com/subscribe" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><strong>Subscribe</strong></a>&nbsp;the fastest growing AI Newsletter and join the elite group of 1500+ readers.</p></blockquote></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*0tPprYtXo6fFo-cM', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Online Courses'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Frank Harris')),
    (UUID(), 'Brain Training For Dogs- Online Course By Adrienne Farricelli', 'The "Brain Training for Dogs" online course by Adrienne Farricelli introduces a unique, science-backed approach to improving dog behavior through mental stimulation and positive reinforcement. Unlike outdated or force-based methods, this course taps into a dogs natural intelligence to address root causes of bad behavior and foster obedience and happiness. With step-by-step guides, practical exercises, and expert support, the program covers common challenges like barking, jumping, and anxiety, offering transformative results for $67. Perfect for dog owners seeking an effective, compassionate training solution to build a stronger bond with their pets.', '<div><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*WeCAxTX-LKlA7gS_iCsgCQ.png" alt="" width="700" height="326" /></picture></div></div><figcaption data-selectable-paragraph="">Source: braintraining4dogs.com</figcaption></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Ever wondered why some dogs seem almost human in their understanding and behavior? Well, it might just be the result of some effective dog training. In this blog post, we&rsquo;re diving into a unique approach that&rsquo;s not just about teaching your dog the basics of sit &amp; stay.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">We&rsquo;ll explore the &ldquo;<strong>Brain Training for Dogs</strong>&rdquo; online course by&nbsp;<strong>Adrienne Farricelli</strong>, promising a transformative experience for you and your furry friend. Get ready to unlock the secrets to a happier, more obedient dog, and perhaps even pick up a new trick or two yourself!</p><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 1400w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-testid="og" /><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*Mz1JLnCKmtKBfhjWv4wUoQ.png" alt="" width="700" height="347" /></picture></div></div><figcaption data-selectable-paragraph="">Source: braintraining4dogs.com</figcaption></figure><h2 data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>💡</strong><a href="https://fb2aainc0f5oi8c539ul1016zj.hop.clickbank.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><strong>Learn More About Her</strong></a></h2><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">What Makes My Dog Training System So Unique&hellip;</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">1️⃣A lot of dog training programs today don&rsquo;t work well because they don&rsquo;t help your dog think and learn. When dogs get to use their brains, many bad behaviors go away.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">2️⃣Some training programs&nbsp;<strong>don&rsquo;t fix the real problem</strong>&nbsp;behind why dogs act out. They might stop your dog from biting, chewing, or barking for a little while, but since they don&rsquo;t solve the main issue, the problem can come back.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">3️⃣Many training methods are old and use force, which isn&rsquo;t good. The newest studies show that being kind and gentle with your dog works better. My training is all about being nice to your dog, helping you two become closer, and making sure your dog feels happy, not scared. We focus on the good things your dog does.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">4️⃣Be careful of online dog training by people who don&rsquo;t have the right training or certificates. If you use the wrong methods, your dog&rsquo;s behavior could get worse, and it might even bite. It&rsquo;s important to listen to trainers who have the right education and certificates.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">Who Needs This Secret to using your dog&rsquo;s natural intelligence to stop bad behavior?</h1><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Does any of the following sound familiar&hellip;</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">🐾Your dog&nbsp;<strong>doesn&rsquo;t listen to you</strong><br />🐾You need to&nbsp;<strong>train a new Puppy</strong><br />🐾Your dog&nbsp;<strong>barks uncontrollably</strong><br />🐾Your Dog is&nbsp;<strong>pulling on the leash</strong><br />🐾Your Dog is&nbsp;<strong>reactive</strong><br />🐾Your Dog is&nbsp;<strong>chewing</strong>&nbsp;things he shouldn&rsquo;t<br />🐾Your Dog is&nbsp;<strong>digging all the time</strong><br />🐾Your Dog is&nbsp;<strong>Jumping up</strong><br />🐾You&rsquo;re frustrated with your dog<br />🐾You may even&nbsp;<strong>regret getting your Dog</strong><br />🐾You feel&nbsp;<strong>helpless to control your dog</strong><br />🐾You tell your Dog &lsquo;no&rsquo; with no success<br />🐾Your Dog&nbsp;<strong>gets over excited</strong>&nbsp;and is hard to settle down<br />🐾Your Dog is&nbsp;<strong>whining constantly</strong><br />🐾<strong>Your dog has a fear</strong>&nbsp;of certain sounds or stimuli or suffers from&nbsp;<strong>anxiety</strong><br />🐾You want a dog who obeys you<br />🐾You want a better bond with your dog<br />🐾You want less stress</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong><em>I can teach you some easy tricks to fix almost any kind of trouble you&rsquo;re having. It&rsquo;s going to be simple and fast!</em></strong></p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">The Science behind my dog training system</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">My method for fixing bad dog habits is really straightforward.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Have you ever heard about how our brains can change and learn new things all the time?</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Scientists at big schools like&nbsp;<strong>Harvard</strong>&nbsp;study this a lot. It means our brains are kind of like soft playdough that can be shaped to learn new stuff.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Guess what? Your dog&rsquo;s brain works the same way! With fun games and the right kind of training in my program, your dog&rsquo;s brain will get better at picking up new things.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Your dog will start listening to you</strong>&nbsp;more and understand what you want him to do.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">When this happens, the naughty things your dog does will start to disappear, and good behaviors will take their place.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Why ANYBODY can use my system to eradicate bad behaviors and have a really well behaved Dog?</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">🐶<strong>Because I cover every conceivable problem</strong>&nbsp;you can have with your dog and show you how to change it including:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">🐕&zwj;🦺Potty training<br />🐕&zwj;🦺Lunging<br />🐕&zwj;🦺Jumping<br />🐕&zwj;🦺Digging<br />🐕&zwj;🦺Whining<br />🐕&zwj;🦺Chewing<br />🐕&zwj;🦺Excessive barking<br />🐕&zwj;🦺Impulse control<br />🐕&zwj;🦺Hyperactivity<br />🐕&zwj;🦺Ignoring your commands<br />🐕&zwj;🦺And much more&hellip;</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">🐶<strong>Because I made a special guide</strong>&nbsp;that makes it super easy to teach your dog and fix any naughty things they do. It&rsquo;s like a fun paint-by-numbers game, but for training your dog! I put together all the best tips from years of helping lots of different dogs. I&rsquo;ll show you how it all works, step by step, with pictures and videos too, so you can have a really good dog friend without it being hard or confusing.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">👩🏻&zwj;💻<strong>Because I&rsquo;m here to personally help</strong>&nbsp;you with my easy support system. I know a lot and can help you do well.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">📋<strong>Because you get a HUGE archive</strong>&nbsp;that talks about almost every kind of dog problem you can think of. It has special answers for different problems that really get to the heart of why they happen. All of this is made by someone who knows a lot about dogs and has been teaching them for a long time.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">⚙️<strong>Because you get a simple-to-follow process.</strong>&nbsp;Every good dog trainer will say keeping it simple is best for teaching dogs to behave well. My way of training is really easy to understand. It&rsquo;s like it shows you all the steps to make your dog behave nicely and not have any problems.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">🔰<strong>Because I&rsquo;m sharing special tips with you that have been proven to work for training dogs</strong>. This isn&rsquo;t just guesswork; these methods have been used in real life and they really work.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">🐕<strong>Because you find out the real reason</strong>&nbsp;for each problem your dog has, like chewing, barking, or acting out around other dogs or people. Then, you get a special solution for each problem. Most dog training programs don&rsquo;t work well because they try to use one big solution for everything, and they don&rsquo;t see your dog as unique.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Now Let&rsquo;s Talk About Your Investment</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">If you had someone come to your house to train your dog, it could cost you&nbsp;<strong>$350 for just one hour</strong>. If they stayed the whole day to help, you might have to pay $3,300. People really do pay that much!</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">But guess what? I have a special way to teach your dog that won&rsquo;t cost you so much. It&rsquo;s&nbsp;<strong>not $400</strong>, it&rsquo;s&nbsp;<strong>not $200</strong>, and it&rsquo;s&nbsp;<strong>not even $100</strong>. You can learn all my dog training secrets for&nbsp;<strong>just $67</strong>!</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">That&rsquo;s right,&nbsp;<strong>only $67</strong>&nbsp;to learn everything I know about making your dog listen, behave, and be super smart and happy.</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Think about it. As soon as you start learning from me&hellip;</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">You&rsquo;ll be able to fix any naughty thing your dog does, and help them be their best smart and good self.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">This is really important stuff that could be worth a lot to you.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">📢&nbsp;<a href="https://fb2aainc0f5oi8c539ul1016zj.hop.clickbank.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><strong>And I&rsquo;m only asking for $67 for it</strong></a></h2><h2 data-selectable-paragraph=""><a href="https://fb2aainc0f5oi8c539ul1016zj.hop.clickbank.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">To learn more about this revolutionary training method , visit today!</a></h2></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*WeCAxTX-LKlA7gS_iCsgCQ.png', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Online Courses'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Frank Harris')),
    (UUID(), 'Purchasing Power Parity For Online Courses', 'Purchasing Power Parity (PPP) plays a vital role in pricing online courses globally, ensuring affordability and accessibility for diverse markets. ParityVend leverages PPP to adjust course prices based on visitors locations, expanding reach, boosting sales, and maximizing profits. This platform provides No-Code and API solutions for easy integration, anti-fraud measures to secure pricing, and analytics to optimize strategies. By adopting ParityVend, businesses can emulate industry leaders like Netflix and Adobe, effectively tailoring pricing for global audiences. ParityVend offers a free plan to help businesses grow and succeed in the global e-learning market.', '<div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Have you ever wondered why a Big Mac costs more in Switzerland than in India? Or why a Netflix subscription is cheaper in Brazil than in the UK? The answer is&nbsp;<strong>purchasing power parity (PPP)</strong>, a concept that compares the relative value of different currencies in terms of what they can buy in their respective markets.</p><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 1400w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-testid="og" /><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg" alt="" width="700" height="394" /></picture></div></div><figcaption data-selectable-paragraph="">ParityVend: online courses</figcaption></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">PPP is important for&nbsp;<strong>online courses</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>e-learning</strong>, especially in the context of&nbsp;<strong>globalization</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>digital business</strong>. If you are selling an online course to customers around the world, you need to consider how much they can afford to pay for it. If you charge the same price in every country, you might be losing potential customers who find your course too expensive, or leaving money on the table by underpricing your course in some markets.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">That&rsquo;s why you need&nbsp;<strong>ParityVend</strong>, a platform that helps businesses go global by adjusting prices based on each visitor&rsquo;s location, using PPP as a key factor. ParityVend allows you to offer your online course at prices that match the purchasing power of different markets, making it more affordable and accessible worldwide. This can expand your customer base, increase your sales, and optimize your profits.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">How does ParityVend work, and what are its main features and benefits? Let&rsquo;s find out.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">How ParityVend Adjusts Prices Based on PPP</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">ParityVend helps you find the optimal price for your online course in each country, based on the PPP index and purchasing power in it.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">For example, let&rsquo;s say you are selling an online course for $100 in the US. You can use ParityVend to automatically adjust the price for each visitor, depending on where they are from. A visitor from India might see the price as $50 (₹4,100), while a visitor from Brazil might see it as $70 (346 Brazilian Real). These prices reflect the&nbsp;<strong>purchasing power&nbsp;</strong>of each market, making your online course more attractive and competitive.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">ParityVend also provides a special &ldquo;No-Code&rdquo; banner that informs your visitors about the price adjustment and the savings they can get by buying your online course. This can increase trust and conversion rates, as well as reduce cart abandonment.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">How ParityVend Protects Businesses from Fraud and Abuse</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">One of the challenges of adjusting prices based on PPP is that some visitors might try to take advantage of the system by using tools like VPN, proxy, TOR, bots, or scrapers to access your online course at a lower price. This can harm your business and your revenue.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">That&rsquo;s why ParityVend offers powerful anti-abuse systems that detect and prevent fraudulent activities on your website. ParityVend identifies visitors who use VPN, proxy, TOR, bots, or scrapers, ensuring a secure pricing environment. You can also customize your anti-abuse settings, such as choosing which countries to allow or deny.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">How ParityVend Provides Insights and Analytics</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">ParityVend also helps you monitor and improve your pricing strategies by providing real-time banner previews and detailed statistics. You can see what your online course price looks like in different countries, and how it changes according to the PPP index and the exchange rate. You can also see how many visitors you get from each country. ParityVend&rsquo;s insights and analytics can help you optimize your pricing strategies, identify new opportunities, and measure your performance.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">No-Code and API Solutions</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">ParityVend offers two solutions to suit your needs and preferences:&nbsp;<strong>No-Code&nbsp;</strong>and&nbsp;<strong>API</strong>.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The No-Code solution provides an easy and user-friendly experience, perfect for solopreneurs, low-code businesses, or startups. It allows you to quickly expand worldwide in less than seven minutes, without writing a single line of code. You can choose from 99 pre-built presets and a variety of customization options, such as country grouping methods, banner texts, styles, and positions. You don&rsquo;t need any technical skills to set up ParityVend No-Code on your website &mdash; the integration process is beginner-friendly and simple.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The API solution offers strong and customizable features, allowing you to create custom pricing flows that fit your unique needs and goals. This is ideal for SaaS companies, startups, and enterprises. You can use ParityVend&rsquo;s API to implement advanced functionality.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">How ParityVend Helps Businesses Achieve Success and Growth</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">ParityVend is not just a platform, it&rsquo;s a partner that helps businesses achieve success and growth in the global market. By using ParityVend, businesses can position themselves alongside industry leaders like Netflix, Spotify, Apple, Microsoft, and Adobe, who all successfully adapt their pricing strategies to global markets based on PPP.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Conclusion</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Purchasing power parity is a concept that can help you sell your online course to more customers around the world, by adjusting your prices based on each visitor&rsquo;s location. ParityVend is a platform that makes this process easy and effective, by providing you with plenty of features and benefits.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">If you want to take your online course and e-learning business to the next level, you should try ParityVend today. Visit ParityVend&rsquo;s website and sign up for a free plan (it&rsquo;s truly free! No credit card needed).</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Learn more about ParityVend and the full list of its features on its official website:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ambeteco.com/ParityVend/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">https://www.ambeteco.com/ParityVend/</a></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Get ParityVend now:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ambeteco.com/ParityVend/pricing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">https://www.ambeteco.com/ParityVend/pricing/</a></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Take a look at the live demos.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">API demo:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ambeteco.com/ParityVend/api-demo/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">https://www.ambeteco.com/ParityVend/api-demo/</a></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">No-Code demo:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ambeteco.com/ParityVend/no-code-demo/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">https://www.ambeteco.com/ParityVend/no-code-demo/</a></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*86sRABsqIsFjOsyzy-b52w.jpeg', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Online Courses'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Frank Harris')),
    (UUID(), 'Enhance Your Online Course Creation with Netjet.io', 'In the evolving world of online education, Netjet.io emerges as a leading platform for creating dynamic and engaging course content. Designed with educators in mind, Netjet.io combines an intuitive drag-and-drop interface with a library of pre-designed templates and interactive elements to streamline course creation. Its responsiveness ensures seamless learning experiences across devices, while features like quizzes and multimedia integration enhance learner engagement. By prioritizing accessibility, customization, and mobile optimization, Netjet.io empowers educators of all skill levels to craft professional and interactive online courses, bridging education and innovation.', '<div><div><div><article><div><div><section><div><div><div><div><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*MHTJrwRJs4DdcXBbRPN_Jg.png" alt="" width="700" height="700" /></picture></div></div></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">In the dynamic landscape of online education, choosing the right platform for course creation is pivotal.&nbsp;<a href="https://www.netjet.io/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Netjet.io</a>, a versatile and user-friendly website builder, emerges as the perfect solution for educators aiming to enhance their online courses. Here&rsquo;s why Netjet.io stands out as the ideal choice for crafting compelling and engaging educational experiences.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">1. Intuitive Drag-and-Drop Interface:<br /><a href="https://www.netjet.io/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Netjet.io</a>&nbsp;boasts a remarkably intuitive drag-and-drop interface, designed with educators in mind. This user-friendly approach makes it accessible for educators of all technical levels to create visually appealing and interactive course content. With Netjet.io, the focus remains on the substance of the courses rather than grappling with complex design tools.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The simplicity of the drag-and-drop interface ensures that educators can effortlessly design and organize course materials. This accessibility empowers educators to spend more time on curriculum development and less time navigating intricate design features.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">2. Pre-designed Blocks and Templates:<br /><a href="https://www.netjet.io/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Netjet.io</a>&nbsp;offers a rich library of pre-designed blocks and templates specifically tailored for educational content. Educators can select from a variety of layouts and styles to create visually cohesive and professional-looking course pages. This not only saves time but also ensures a consistent and polished presentation.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The availability of ready-made blocks and templates accelerates the course creation process, enabling educators to maintain a visually engaging and cohesive online learning environment. It strikes the perfect balance between customization and efficiency.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">3. Interactive Elements for Engaging Learning:<br />Netjet.io provides an array of interactive elements, including forms, quizzes, and multimedia integration. These features allow educators to create dynamic and engaging lessons, fostering active participation and enhancing the overall learning experience.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Interactive elements are essential for keeping learners engaged. Netjet.io&rsquo;s incorporation of these features ensures that educators can transform traditional content into immersive and interactive learning modules.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">4. Responsiveness and Mobile Optimization:<br />In the era of mobile learning, Netjet.io shines with its responsive design capabilities. Course content created with Netjet.io automatically adapts to various screen sizes, providing a seamless experience for learners on desktops, tablets, and smartphones.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">With the increasing prevalence of mobile devices, ensuring that online courses are accessible on various platforms is crucial. Netjet.io&rsquo;s commitment to mobile optimization guarantees that educators can reach and engage with a broader audience.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Conclusion: Netjet.io &mdash; Where Education Meets Innovation<br />Netjet.io&rsquo;s fusion of simplicity, versatility, and powerful features makes it an exceptional choice for educators venturing into the realm of online courses. Whether you&rsquo;re an experienced e-learning professional or a newcomer to the field, Netjet.io provides the tools and resources needed to create captivating and effective educational content. Revolutionize your online courses with Netjet.io, where education seamlessly meets innovation.</p></div></div></div></div></section></div></div></article></div>&nbsp;</div></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*MHTJrwRJs4DdcXBbRPN_Jg.png', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Online Courses'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Eve Wilson')),
    (UUID(), 'Benefits of Virtual Education: Is It Better Than Classroom Learning?', 'Virtual education has transformed modern learning by offering flexibility, personalized experiences, diverse resources, and global collaboration opportunities. It enhances accessibility for individuals with disabilities and reduces costs, making education more inclusive and affordable. While traditional classrooms provide valuable face-to-face interaction, virtual learnings adaptability to individual needs and technological advancements positions it as a compelling alternative. Balancing the strengths of both approaches could shape the future of a learner-centric educational experience.', '<div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><article><div><div><section><div><div><div><div><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*pOOa0NvoNAaYug2GIjg_kg.png" alt="" width="700" height="389" /></picture></div></div></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">In recent years, virtual education has gained significant traction as technology continues to revolutionize the way we learn. With the advent of online platforms, video conferencing tools, and interactive learning environments, the debate surrounding virtual education versus traditional classroom learning has become increasingly relevant.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">In this article, we will delve into the advantages of virtual education, exploring its potential benefits and comparing them to the traditional classroom setting.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">By examining the key aspects of both approaches, we aim to shed light on whether virtual education holds an edge over conventional classroom learning.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Flexibility and Convenience</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">One of the most notable advantages of virtual education is its flexibility and convenience. Unlike traditional classrooms, virtual education allows learners to access course materials at their own pace and convenience.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Students can attend classes from anywhere in the world, eliminating geographical constraints and saving time associated with commuting.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">This flexibility empowers learners to balance their education with work, personal commitments, or other responsibilities, making education more accessible to a broader range of individuals.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Personalized Learning Experience</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Virtual education offers personalized learning experiences tailored to individual needs. Online platforms often integrate adaptive learning technologies that track students&rsquo; progress and adapt the curriculum accordingly.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">This approach ensures that each learner receives targeted instruction and support based on their strengths, weaknesses, and learning style.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">By tailoring the content and pace to individual needs, virtual education enhances comprehension, engagement, and overall academic performance.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Diverse Learning Resources</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Virtual education opens up a vast array of learning resources that may not be readily available in a traditional classroom setting.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Through online platforms, students gain access to multimedia materials, e-books, interactive simulations, and educational websites. These resources enhance the learning experience by providing diverse perspectives, real-world examples, and interactive exercises that cater to different learning preferences.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Additionally, virtual education encourages self-directed learning, empowering students to explore topics beyond the confines of a textbook.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Global Collaborations and Networking</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Virtual education breaks down geographical barriers, enabling students to collaborate with peers from around the world.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Online discussion forums, video conferences, and group projects facilitate cross-cultural exchanges and foster global networking opportunities. By interacting with individuals from different backgrounds, virtual education promotes cultural understanding, broadens perspectives, and enhances teamwork and communication skills.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Such global collaborations prepare students for the increasingly interconnected nature of our world.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Enhanced Accessibility and Inclusivity</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">For individuals facing physical disabilities, virtual education provides an inclusive learning environment. Online platforms can be designed to accommodate various accessibility requirements, such as closed captioning, screen readers, and alternative input devices.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">This ensures that learners with disabilities have equal access to education, empowering them to pursue their academic goals without facing significant barriers.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Additionally, virtual education eliminates some of the socio-economic disparities associated with traditional classroom learning, making education more accessible to individuals from disadvantaged backgrounds.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Cost-Effectiveness</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Virtual education often proves to be a cost-effective alternative to traditional classroom setups. It eliminates expenses associated with commuting, transportation, and accommodation.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Moreover, online courses tend to have lower tuition fees compared to their on-campus counterparts. Virtual education also reduces expenses related to textbooks, as digital materials and resources are often included in the course fee or available at more affordable prices.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">These cost-saving benefits make education more affordable and accessible to a broader range of learners.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Conclusion</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">While both virtual education and traditional classroom learning have their merits, virtual education offers several distinct advantages that make it a compelling option for many learners.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The flexibility, personalized learning experience, diverse resources, global collaborations, enhanced accessibility, and cost-effectiveness of virtual education contribute to its growing popularity.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">However, it is essential to acknowledge that virtual education may not suit every learner or subject, as face-to-face interactions and hands-on experiences offered in traditional classrooms hold their own value.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Ultimately, the choice between virtual education and classroom learning depends on individual preferences, learning goals, and the specific requirements of the subject matter.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">As technology continues to evolve, the future of education lies in finding a balance that integrates the best aspects of both approaches, creating a truly dynamic and learner-centric educational experience.</p><blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph="">If you have found inspiration and if it has added value to your life, I kindly request your support.&nbsp;<strong>Please buy me a coffee here:&nbsp;</strong><a href="https://www.buymeacoffee.com/PepTalkRadio" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><strong>https://www.buymeacoffee.com/PepTalkRadio</strong></a></p></blockquote></div></div></div></div></section></div></div></article></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*pOOa0NvoNAaYug2GIjg_kg.png', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Classroom Learning'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Grace Taylor')),
    (UUID(), 'Metrics that Matter: How to use VR to transform classroom learning', 'Metrics that Matter: How to Use VR to Transform Classroom Learning explores the transformative potential of virtual reality (VR) in education. By immersing students in dynamic, interactive environments, VR facilitates hands-on learning experiences that transcend traditional classroom boundaries. The article highlights how VR aligns with Webbs Depth of Knowledge taxonomy, fostering progression from knowledge acquisition to complex problem-solving. It also underscores the importance of tools that measure student engagement and growth, enabling teachers to adapt and improve instruction effectively. The piece concludes by advocating for collaboration between educators and developers to create innovative VR solutions that empower teaching and enrich learning outcomes.', '<figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 1400w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC. 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-testid="og" /><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC." alt="" width="700" height="360" /></picture></div></div></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Imagine a school where students work with city planners to develop a new playground during first period, build a working lawn mower to care for the grounds in second period, create life-sized sculptures to exhibit in their space during third period, and by fourth period they&rsquo;re synthesizing biodiesel to fuel the lawn mowers that care for their grounds.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Does this sound like a dream school? It may be reality sooner than you think. With the proliferation of games for learning, virtual reality has the potential to transport children to places out of reach for most students. Students can visit a&nbsp;<a href="https://edu.google.com/expeditions/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">lab where peptides are synthesized to make palliative treatments for cancer patients, an underwater dive to see the giant sea turtles in the Galapagos</a>, or even visit one of&nbsp;<a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/465450/iOMoon/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Jupiter&rsquo;s moons</a>.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">There are at&nbsp;<a href="https://medium.com/@lportnoy/4-ways-virtual-reality-will-change-learning-1d2b291fbe7b" rel="noopener">least four ways VR can change learning</a>&nbsp;and each will be even more profound when paired with tools to help teachers observe, document, and provide feedback while continuing to engage and enlighten students. The creation of these tools requires an understanding of how student learning becomes more complex over time, how to measure what matters, how to align those metrics to the many ways in which students demonstrate their knowledge, and most importantly to identify what tools teachers see as valuable to improve and inform their instruction.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>How Students Learn</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Researchers have shown time and again that learning is dictated by&nbsp;<em>content</em>, not individual&nbsp;<em>ability,&nbsp;</em>rendering the term learning style&nbsp;<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2017/mar/13/teachers-neuromyth-learning-styles-scientists-neuroscience-education" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">defunct</a>. Students learn through a variety of modes including visual, auditory, kinesthetic and over&nbsp;<a href="https://cft.vanderbilt.edu/guides-sub-pages/learning-styles-preferences/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">seventy more</a>!</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Would you prefer a cardiothoracic surgeon who fashions herself strictly a visual learner and reads widely about open-heart surgeries, or perhaps you&rsquo;d prefer the person who has listened thoroughly, read widely, and logged thousands of hours in lab perfecting her technique?</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Just as experts hone their craft using a variety of modalities, students acquire knowledge in a multitude of ways. A student can demonstrate learning kinesthetically by creating a physical model or verbally by defending their position in a debate. Depending on the domain it may be more relevant to have a student write a response to an opinion piece or to create a piece of music. Herein lies yet another way that virtual environments can activate the senses, engage multiple modalities, and bring depth and breadth to classroom learning.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Measuring Learning to Improve Instruction</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Measuring learning serves one purpose: to inform teaching and learning. It is not the teacher&rsquo;s goal to stamp a letter on each child&rsquo;s head and place them back on the assembly line for next year&rsquo;s teacher. The science behind the best methods of&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ascd.org/publications/books/111005/chapters/Section-1@-What-Is-Formative-Assessment%C2%A2.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">formative assessment</a>&nbsp;relies upon cognitive taxonomies. These taxonomies map learning as a progression from simple to complex demonstrations of knowledge and are used by educators to delineate student learning.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><a href="http://www.webbalign.org/dok-training.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Webb&rsquo;s</a>&nbsp;is the most widely used taxonomy for demonstrating knowledge across a variety of&nbsp;<a href="http://ossucurr.pbworks.com/w/file/fetch/49691156/Norm%20web%20dok%20by%20subject%20area.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">domains</a>&nbsp;across four successive levels of knowing: acquisition, application, analysis, and augmentation of knowledge. As students move from one level to the next, they are tasked with showing their knowledge in increasingly complex ways. For example, the acquisition level (DOK 1) requires simple recall of knowledge such as naming the three branches of government, whereas the augmentation level (DOK 4) pushes the student to apply acquired knowledge in a novel or distinct way such as analyzing the ways in which the United States government was created based on ancient Greece.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">In virtual reality environments we can scaffold a student&rsquo;s demonstration of knowledge by providing tools to increase engagement while providing metrics to show growth along a learning progression. These environments show student&rsquo;s actions and interactions with content making their knowledge visible and ripe for the qualitatively rich metrics that measure growth and development.</p><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 1400w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW. 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-testid="og" /><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*4pzknigJZkX0k_RW." alt="" width="700" height="224" /></picture></div></div></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Pairing Measurement with Authentic Learning in VR Environments</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Let&rsquo;s break down each level of learning in Webb&rsquo;s taxonomy and see how&nbsp;<a href="https://medium.com/@lportnoy/4-ways-virtual-reality-will-change-learning-1d2b291fbe7b" rel="noopener">VR has the potential to improve learning</a>&nbsp;and provide meaningful feedback on that learning to inform instruction. Taken point by point here&rsquo;s why:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><em>1: Acquisition and the Ability to Touch</em></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">In physical reality students can sort items in an array, identify the atoms of a molecules, or simply select a book off the shelf that will help them finish their book report. These human experiences embedded in virtual reality will allow users to touch items in a virtual world in an effort to demonstrating knowledge acquisition (DOK 1).</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Exploring in a virtual world may find students sort the same array or identify those same molecules, but they can also seek out definitions to secure basic content knowledge by selecting items in a virtual world even with the most rudimentary of VR viewers.&nbsp;<a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.drashvr.titansofspacecb&amp;hl=en_GB" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Titans of Space</a>&nbsp;is one experience where students take a tour of the planets in our solar system and learn basic facts about things like the rings of Saturn and nearby stars. A student&rsquo;s selection of items can be provided to teachers as feedback to show just which components they were most engaged in learning about and serves as a launching point from which to extend learning to deeper levels of inquiry like DOK 2.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><em>2: Application and the Capacity to Manipulate</em></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The application level or DOK 2 requires students to process information through actions such as summarizing or predicting where learners manipulate simple knowledge to demonstrate how they have reorganized content into meaningful knowledge. In a physical space this often looks like the summary of a story, the creation of a diorama, or performing a piece based on a reading.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">In virtual worlds these same skills can be demonstrated but with greater detail and with the capacity to document anf therefore better capture and honor each movement. For example, a student who uses the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TckqNdrdbgk" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">tilt brush</a>&nbsp;to retell a story with drawings or creates their own diorama in VR using&nbsp;<a href="https://blog.cospaces.io/making-an-interactive-vr-infographic-5c20fe5d29e6" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">CoSpaces</a>&nbsp;leaves an image forever secured in space, which can be toured by other students and the teacher. What&rsquo;s more it provides useful feedback about how the student applied information (DOK 2) from discrete facts (DOK 1) while generating feedback to the teacher to move beyond application (DOK 2) and into the realm of higher order thinking and problem solving apparent in DOK 3.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><em>3: Analysis and the Tools to Create</em></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The third level of Webb&rsquo;s taxonomy is Analysis, which speaks to the student&rsquo;s ability to go beyond the surface of understanding and processing information towards evaluating perspectives, investigating alternative sources of information, and solving problems. In a classroom this often looks like drawing conclusions from observations in science, questioning primary and secondary sources in history, or using different theorems to solve an equation in math.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Virtual spaces provide student&rsquo;s with a template to create materials that support their ideas. Consider a high school trigonometry class where students learn about sine, cosine, and tangent. They&rsquo;ve mastered DOK 1 and 2 by identifying and recalling each term but in DOK 3 they need to demonstrate their ability to solve problems using these functions. A student could demonstrate this knowledge by solving problems in a virtual world where the height of trees dictates where they should be placed in a community garden or in proximity to a school building. This is similar to the real work of&nbsp;<a href="https://archpaper.com/2017/04/gensler-nvidia-new-headquarters/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">architects embracing VR</a>&nbsp;who are working to create more authentic representations of their projects, bridging the virtual and physical world while setting the stage for knowledge to move from analysis (DOK 3) to augmentation (DOK 4).</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><em>4: Augmentation of Knowledge and the Potential to Change</em></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Augmentation (DOK 4) encompasses the cognitive abilities of each of the levels that come before. A student must be able to solve a problem using sine in DOK 3 which also includes their ability to define sine (DOK 2) and recognize it as a function in trigonometry (DOK 1). The final level of augmentation (DOK 4) requires students to have embraced levels one through three while adding on the cognitive complexity of formulating strategies to solve new problems, restructuring of data, or generating novel hypotheses. DOK 4 requires students to synthesize their knowledge in a way that allows them to solve problems that don&rsquo;t always have easy solutions.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">In a physical setting students may read primary and secondary sources in a history class around causes of the American Civil War ranging from issues of slavery, the state&rsquo;s rights and even Lincoln&rsquo;s election. After reading multiple sources, discussing, and debating, students propose a well-reasoned explanation for the war citing sources and providing evidence to support their assertion. In virtual worlds this exercise can take place through the exploration of multiple immersive learning experiences like&nbsp;<a href="https://www.engadget.com/2017/02/01/my-brothers-keeper-vr-sundance/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">My Brother&rsquo;s Keeper</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href="http://www.discoveryvr.com/watch/urban-warfare/details" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Urban Warfare</a>&nbsp;with the added bonus of activating embodied cognition, cultivating&nbsp;<a href="https://medium.com/@lportnoy/the-neural-technology-of-empathy-and-the-virtual-technology-that-will-harness-it-2a5e89e11de3" rel="noopener">empathy</a>, and providing additional layers of understanding from traditional texts.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Documenting Growth While Empowering Educators</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Students learn best when they have a knowledgeable guide, access to requisite tools for acquiring knowledge, and when their teachers are given the autonomy to observe, document, and collect feedback to inform their teaching. By understanding the range of cognitive skills students demonstrate while learning, VR experiences can provide that feedback in real time during each immersive experience to fuel repeated engagement and qualitatively rich information to guide instruction. To do this well we must continue to ask important questions about the user&rsquo;s experience as we develop immersive learning experiences. For instance, how will environments allow students to move, manipulate, and create representations of their learning? And how will developers provide teachers with a template to connect immersive experiences in virtual worlds to the synthesis of knowledge in the physical world through reading, writing, and presenting student work?</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Teachers are master storytellers who craft engaging lessons and tailor assessments that drive future instruction each and every day. If VR developers want to harness the power of their technology to boost learning and provide meaningful feedback they will need to work closely with professional educators. Together we can create tools to best support student growth and learning by considering: What are the most intuitive ways to build interactions within an immersive experience? How will you measure these interactions? Which level of cognition is enacted in each action? What is the best way to deliver formative assessment to teachers to best inform their instruction? Where will you provide scaffolds to deepen learning or support struggling students during these experiences?</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The important takeaway is that&nbsp;<mark>these tools have not yet been created so the field is ripe for innovation in developing metrics that matter most to teachers to fuel learning</mark>. Together we can create immersive experiences that are rich in formative assessments to support teachers while captivating students to ensure that they continue to learn, grow, and keep coming back for more.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">***</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><em>Lindsay Portnoy is co-Founder and Chief Learning Officer of&nbsp;</em><a href="http://www.killersnails.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><em>Killer Snails</em></a><em>, a gaming company that uses extreme creatures of nature to build immersive and engaging learning experiences aligned to meaningful assessments that support educators.</em></p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><em>Connect via&nbsp;</em><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/lblauportnoy" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><em>LinkedIn</em></a><em>,&nbsp;</em><a href="https://twitter.com/lportnoy" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><em>Twitter</em></a><em>, or&nbsp;</em><a href="http://lindsay@killersnails.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><em>email</em></a><em>.</em></p>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*QwAgU57d1sbdyOpC.', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Classroom Learning'), FALSE, 89, '2024-02-01 14:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Grace Taylor')),
    (UUID(), 'Can E-Learning Replace Classroom Learning?', 'Online education has challenged traditional stereotypes, offering flexibility, accessibility, and cost-effectiveness that traditional classroom learning often lacks. While some critics question the legitimacy of online degrees, the advantages of e-learning are hard to ignore. These include the ability to study diverse subjects from prestigious institutions, the comfort of learning from home, the resume-enhancing value of certifications, and the flexibility of self-paced schedules that cater to working professionals and parents. Additionally, online courses are significantly more affordable, with many being offered for free. Despite these benefits, e-learning also requires self-discipline and a conducive study environment. As online education continues to grow, it is reshaping how we approach learning, blending convenience with quality education to meet the demands of modern learners.', '<p><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*Or-XO0U1bQa5KblyRerwtg.jpeg" alt="" /></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Online education has many stereotypes about it. People often think that online students are not smart enough for our usual college or university education. They are lazy and do not get &ldquo;real&rdquo; degrees. These thoughts discourage many people from taking online courses, so they get stuck in the traditional educational system, which wastes a lot of money, nerves and years of their lives.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Let&rsquo;s look closer at the benefits and disadvantages of&nbsp;<a href="https://shakuro.com/blog/e-learning-trends-for-2022" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">online learning</a>&nbsp;that can make you reconsider your attitude towards this type of e-business.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">What are the advantages of online learning?</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>1. You can learn whatever you want!</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The mobile e-learning market surpassed&nbsp;<a href="https://financesonline.com/25-essential-learning-management-system-e-learning-statistics-analysis-of-trends-data-and-market-share/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">$38 billion</a>&nbsp;by the end of 2021. With online courses, you can take any program or course at traditional four-year universities.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">For example, if you are interested in neuroscience, all it takes is a Google search for such an online course and you will easily find online programs offered by some of the most prestigious universities from around the world. You can take such a course even if you have no desire to apply this knowledge in your future profession, but you are just interested in discovering new interests and understanding how the human brain works. The wide variety of online programs and courses is a tremendous advantage of this type of education. No matter where you live and what you want to study, you can always find the right course or even a degree program that you can follow from home.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>2. Comfort</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Forget about having to attend classes for hours, sit in an uncomfortable chair and suffer from back pain by the end of the day. All lectures and required materials are provided through online platforms, so you can easily access them from the comfort of your home. Public transportation won&rsquo;t get you to campus. You won&rsquo;t have to spend money on gas for your car. You won&rsquo;t have to get up early to get dressed for class, etc.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Comfort is a strong advantage in the age of&nbsp;<a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/ilkerkoksal/2020/05/02/the-rise-of-online-learning/?sh=567af81b72f3" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">rising online education</a>, but it can go both ways. You shouldn&rsquo;t let yourself get too comfortable when studying at home, so it&rsquo;s best to leave the couch for a few hours a day and create an inspiring study environment in your home. All you need is a large table and a nice comfortable chair. Some online platforms we&rsquo;re working with, like&nbsp;<a href="https://shakuro.com/works/cgma/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">CG Master Academy</a>, have convenient built-in academic calendars that allow you to plan your schedule:</p><figure><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 1400w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-testid="og" /><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png" alt="" width="700" height="299" /></picture></div></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>3. Online courses look great on resumes</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">It doesn&rsquo;t matter where your career is right now; an online program will always look good on your resume. This will show potential employers that you are eager to learn and want to gain more knowledge and new skills. By earning a good certificate or diploma after online training, you are sure to be a better candidate for a promotion and your resume will look much better when you apply for a new position or vacancy.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>4. Self-study</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">When you browse interesting online courses and programs, you will see the Self-Paced label on most of them. What does it mean? Self-paced learning means that students start tasks &zwnj;and they create a learning schedule that suits their individual needs. When you go to college, you can forget about work, hobbies and even family. Under such conditions, studying is a priority. Therefore, many single parents and working people choose to forget all about their dreams in order to get a higher degree.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autodidacticism" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">&nbsp;self-learning system</a>&nbsp;allows them to progress at a pace that suits them. This type of system does not require lecture attendance; You can access the materials at any time convenient for you. If you have to work or take care of your home and children during the day, you can study at night. This is an advantage that the education system we are accustomed to cannot surpass.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>5. Cost reduction</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">According to&nbsp;<a href="https://skillscouter.com/online-learning-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Skill Scouter</a>, 40% of Fortune 500 companies use e-learning and a correlation between eLearning usage and successful companies.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The fact that online programs are cheaper than those offered at colleges or institutes is enough to convince you to consider them. The average fee for online courses depends on several factors, so it varies from one program to another. We&rsquo;ve saved the best part for last: many online courses are completely free. For example,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.mit.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">MIT</a>&nbsp;offers all course materials online at no cost. Free courses rarely come with a certificate of completion, but they are still more than useful for those who want to learn from prestigious educators. Online courses and programs are more convenient and cheaper than their counterparts in traditional education.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The best thing about online learning is that you can learn at ease. All you need is a passion for learning and a good internet connection to get you on the right course.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> ', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*S1HUGFJNojBSqI9V.png', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Classroom Learning'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Grace Taylor')),
    (UUID(), 'Three ways teachers are reimagining classroom learning with Code.org', 'Code.org is transforming traditional computer science classrooms by fostering a collaborative, student-centered learning environment. Three key strategies used by educators are helping to engage students and improve their learning experiences. First, pair programming encourages active collaboration, where students work as "drivers" and "navigators," solving problems together and enhancing communication skills. Second, teachers take on the role of "lead learners," guiding students through challenges without always providing the answers, which fosters independent problem-solving and student responsibility. Lastly, creating an environment where failure is accepted as part of the learning process allows students to embrace iterative learning and collaborative support. By implementing these strategies, Code.orgs curriculum encourages creativity, teamwork, and resilience, making computer science more accessible and engaging for all students.','<div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong><em>About the series:</em></strong>&ldquo;<em>What Does a&nbsp;</em><a href="https://slack-redir.net/link?url=http%3A%2F%2FCode.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><em>Code.org</em></a><em>&nbsp;Classroom Look Like?&rdquo; is a series of blog posts exploring the features that make&nbsp;</em><a href="https://slack-redir.net/link?url=http%3A%2F%2FCode.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><em>Code.org</em></a><em>&nbsp;professional development and curricula unique and engaging for both teachers and students. This is blog post two of four. Read the first post here: &ldquo;</em><a href="https://medium.com/@codeorg/what-does-a-code-org-classroom-look-like-teachers-using-diverse-strategies-to-bring-cs-to-schools-cc02c3b61306" rel="noopener"><em>Five ways teachers are bringing computer science to their schools</em></a><em>.&rdquo;</em></p><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 1400w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-testid="og" /><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg" alt="" width="700" height="467" /></picture></div></div></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Code.org classrooms are often lively places, filled with sounds and sights you might not expect to find in computer science classrooms: students chatting and laughing in pairs or groups, asking each other questions, riffing on ideas,&nbsp;<a href="https://twitter.com/CorpusChristiNJ/status/1207009311945379840" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">even dancing</a>. For many teachers used to computer classes with each student hunched and staring at their own computers in silence, this comes as a welcome surprise. But it&rsquo;s no accident.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">An active, collaborative classroom culture engages students and fosters better learning and increased interest in computer science, so collaboration is something our education team actively incorporates into our courses. There are a number of strategies and activities built into the curriculum and taught at our professional development workshops. Below are just a handful that teachers told us were especially useful in their classrooms.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">You drive, I&rsquo;ll navigate</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">In Demetra Adams&rsquo; K-2 classrooms in Prichard, Alabama, turning students into drivers and navigators during coding activities has been the key to unlocking student engagement.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">&ldquo;We love it!&rdquo; she says. &ldquo;They know, when you&rsquo;re the driver, you&rsquo;re driving the computer, and when you&rsquo;re the navigator, you&rsquo;re helping the driver. They treat it like it&rsquo;s a game, they cheer like it&rsquo;s a game.&rdquo;</p><figure><figcaption>Communication is key to successful pair programming.</figcaption></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">One of the coolest things about pair programming, according to Adams, is that it teaches students life skills, like working through differences to achieve a common goal, in addition to helping facilitate their computer science learning.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">&ldquo;They have ongoing conversations,&rdquo; she says. &ldquo;They&rsquo;ll disagree with each other, but my rule is, you have to be able to resolve it without me coming over, and they almost always figure it out.&rdquo; In fact, Adams says, many of the students who struggle with behavioral problems in other courses excel at computer science and feel confident enough to help others!</p><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 1400w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-testid="og" /><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*dK0Lx87qvOzAyjtnjR5X2g.jpeg" alt="" width="700" height="934" /></picture></div></div><figcaption data-selectable-paragraph="">Students pair-programming in Deby Ranft&rsquo;s class.</figcaption></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Pair programming also helps lower the barrier for schools that don&rsquo;t necessarily have the resources to provide 1:1 technology for their students. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s great because I can pair multiple students up on one computer,&rdquo; says Deby Ranft, whose small school in rural Dayton, Nevada shares wifi with the other schools in the district.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">&ldquo;Any time one student would log in, it kicks off another student in another part of the building, because there are only so many access points,&rdquo; she says.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Instead of students passively waiting and watching, pair programming allows the &ldquo;navigator&rdquo; to lead the activity: because they have to direct the &ldquo;driver&rdquo; on what to do, they&rsquo;re problem-solving and engaging in computational thinking even without controlling the mouse.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">It&rsquo;s easy to get started</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The heart of Code.org&rsquo;s mission is to give every student in every school the chance to learn computer science, and in designing the optimal experience, we want to help people reimagine what classroom learning might look like. Computer science is a deeply collaborative, engaging and creative field, and those are fundamental aspects of our curriculum and pedagogy. And luckily, it&rsquo;s easy to incorporate into your own classroom!</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">If you loved what you read and want to bring computer science to your school,&nbsp;<a href="https://code.org/educate/professional-learning" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">consider taking one of our Professional Learning workshops</a>! Or read our previous post, &ldquo;<a href="https://medium.com/@codeorg/what-does-a-code-org-classroom-look-like-teachers-using-diverse-strategies-to-bring-cs-to-schools-cc02c3b61306" rel="noopener">Five ways teachers are bringing computer science to their schools</a>,&rdquo; for more ideas.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">-Eric Fershtman, Code.org</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>','https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*8FNOM8Rka0PBGCTFYL8osA.jpeg', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Classroom Learning'), FALSE, 89, '2024-02-01 14:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Henry Brown')),
    (UUID(), 'Classroom Learning That Works: Minecraft', 'This article explores the educational potential of Minecraft, a tool often criticized as a "gimmick" in the classroom. The author engages with perspectives from educators, such as Tom Bennett and Stephen Reid, to reflect on how Minecraft can enhance learning. Rather than focusing on student motivation alone, the piece questions how Minecraft enables learners to accomplish previously impossible tasks. Drawing on Robert Marzanos "Classroom Instruction That Works," the article examines how Minecraft aligns with Marzanos strategies, such as fostering cooperation, non-linguistic representations, and helping students extend and apply knowledge. Minecraft is presented not as a distraction but as an opportunity for students to engage in meaningful, creative learning that mirrors real-world skills. The article concludes by advocating for the integration of such technology in education, not as a gimmick, but as a powerful tool for expanding the horizons of what learners can achieve.', '<div><div><div><div><div><div><div><figure><div><picture><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:558/0*O_-O4kdaCpTHuy3g.png" alt="" width="279" height="320" /></picture></div></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">MS Minecraft Certified Trainer badgeReading my Flipboard earlier this month, I ran across a fascinating twitter exchange between Stephen Reid and Tom Bennett. You can find source materials at the bottom of my blog entry. Curious, I decided to dig in and explore some more. As I reflected more and more, I realized that it was all too simple to label gaming a gimmick. And, when I think of Minecraft as a learning platform, it is NOT about&nbsp;<a href="https://gregashman.wordpress.com/2016/11/22/why-microsofts-minecraft-probably-isnt-the-solution/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">capitalizing on student motivation</a>. Rather, it involves asking the same question that we should ask of any technology seeking entrance into our children&rsquo;s learning spaces &mdash; how does it enable learners to accomplish what had previously been impossible?</p><blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong><em>Gimmick:</em></strong><em>&nbsp;a trick or device intended to attract attention, publicity, or business. an ingenious or novel device, scheme, or stratagem, especially one designed to attract attention or increase appeal. (</em><a href="http://www.dictionary.com/browse/gimmick" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><em>Source</em></a><em>)</em></p></blockquote><figure><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/format:webp/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 800w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 400px" /><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png 800w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 400px" data-testid="og" /><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:800/0*5ewuNT8WxUP6tBm7.png" alt="" width="400" height="302" /></picture></div></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><a href="http://www.slideshare.net/ageller/marzano-summarizing-and-note-taking" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">See full-size chart and slideshow</a>&nbsp;this was clipped from.<strong>Respectful Discourse</strong></p><blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><em>I don&rsquo;t want to be disrespectful. Let&rsquo;s have fun exploring inconsistencies and ideas! My purpose for writing this blog entry is to explore my thoughts about Tom Bennett&rsquo;s points and share them with the world. If they are crazy wrong, then please push back in the comments or leave a link to your thoughts in your blog or podcast.</em></p></blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Classroom Instruction That Works</strong><br />As I pondered that question &mdash; achieving the impossible &mdash; I recalled a chart (shown above) featuring Robert Marzano&rsquo;s&nbsp;<em>Classroom Instruction that Works</em>&nbsp;and how each of Marzano&rsquo;s Strategies could enhance student achievement by a certain number of percentile points. Marzano&rsquo;s points can be&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ascd.org/ascd/pdf/siteascd/publications/books/citworks-ell-2nded-excerpts.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">organized in the following way</a>&nbsp;and I&rsquo;m excited about the possibilities:</p><blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Classroom Instruction That Works<em>&nbsp;describes nine categories of instructional strategies that have a high likelihood of improving student achievement. Source: ASCD&rsquo;s&nbsp;</em><a href="http://www.ascd.org/ascd/pdf/siteascd/publications/books/citworks-ell-2nded-excerpts.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><em>Classroom Instruction that Works with English Language Learners</em></a><em>.</em></p></blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph="">I. Creating the Environment for Learning</p><ul><li data-selectable-paragraph="">Setting Objectives and Providing Feedback</li><li data-selectable-paragraph="">Reinforcing Effort and Providing Recognition</li><li data-selectable-paragraph="">Cooperative Learning</li></ul><p data-selectable-paragraph="">II. Helping Students Develop Understanding</p><ul><li data-selectable-paragraph="">Cues, Questions, and Advance Organizers</li><li data-selectable-paragraph="">Nonlinguistic Representations</li><li data-selectable-paragraph="">Summarizing and Note Taking</li><li data-selectable-paragraph="">Assigning Homework and Providing Practice</li></ul><p data-selectable-paragraph="">III. Helping Students Extend and Apply Knowledge</p><ul><li data-selectable-paragraph="">Identifying Similarities and Differences</li><li data-selectable-paragraph="">Generating and Testing Hypotheses</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*O_-O4kdaCpTHuy3g.png', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Classroom Learning'), FALSE, 89, '2024-02-01 14:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Henry Brown')), 
   	(UUID(), 'The Dark Side of AI Domain Name Investing: Avoiding Scams and Fraud', 'AI domain name investing presents lucrative opportunities but is fraught with risks from scams and fraud. Common schemes include fake domain sales, phishing, domain hijacking, trademark infringement, cybersquatting, and dubious AI-themed cryptocurrencies. To safeguard investments, thorough research, secure payment methods, and legal precautions are essential. Investors should verify listings, avoid anonymous cryptocurrency ventures, and understand domain-related legalities like trademark issues and dispute resolution. By staying informed and vigilant, investors can navigate the complexities of AI domain name investing while minimizing financial risks.', '<div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><figure><div><picture><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:582/0*WoGrM10oubWExo35" alt="" width="291" height="173" /></picture></div></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">As AI domain name investing continues to gain popularity, a growing number of investors are falling prey to scams and fraud. Unscrupulous individuals and groups are exploiting the hype surrounding AI and domain names, leaving unsuspecting investors with significant financial losses. In this article, we&rsquo;ll expose the dark side of AI domain name investing and provide valuable tips on how to avoid common scams and fraud.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Common Scams and Fraudulent Schemes</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">1. Fake Domain Name Sales: Scammers create fake domain name listings, often with inflated prices, and convince investors to purchase them. The domain names may not even exist or may be worthless.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">2. Phishing Schemes: Fraudsters send emails or messages appearing to be from reputable domain name marketplaces or registrars, tricking investors into revealing sensitive information or transferring funds to fraudulent accounts.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">3. Domain Name Hijacking: Scammers gain unauthorized access to domain name accounts and transfer ownership or sell the domain names without the rightful owner&rsquo;s consent.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">4. Trademark Infringement: Investors may unknowingly purchase domain names that infringe on existing trademarks, leading to legal disputes and potential financial losses.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">5. Cybersquatting: Scammers register domain names with the intention of selling them to trademark holders at inflated prices.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">6. Cryptocurrency scams: There have been multiple new tokens launched on the back of the AI hype with few offering anything different. Most of these cryptocurrencies are run by anonymous founders. The majority are get-rich-quick schemes for the founders.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Protecting Yourself from Fraud</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">1. Research and Due Diligence: Thoroughly investigate the domain name&rsquo;s history, ownership, and market value before making a purchase.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">2. Verify Listings: Ensure domain name listings are authentic and come from reputable sources.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">3. Secure Payment Methods: Use secure payment methods like escrow services or credit cards, which offer some level of fraud protection.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">4. Domain Name Registry Verification: Verify the domain name&rsquo;s registration and ownership through the relevant registry or registrar.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">5. Legal Advice: Consult with legal experts specializing in domain name disputes and trademark law.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">6. Avoid cryptocurrencies with anonymous founders, they mostly turn out to be scams.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Looking To Start A New Crypto Business? You&rsquo;ll Need A Domain Name For That!</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Whether you&rsquo;re already in the crypto space, planning to enter, or just looking to invest in crypto based domain names,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.coindomain.store/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Coin Domain Store</a>&nbsp;is the platform for you. View our list of premium crypto domain names&nbsp;<a href="https://www.coindomain.store/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">here</a>.</p><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 1400w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-testid="og" /><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*Hr8IOulLn9i5xnhP" alt="" width="700" height="163" /></picture></div></div></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Legal Considerations</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">1. Trademark Infringement: Be aware of existing trademarks and ensure your domain name doesn&rsquo;t infringe on them.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">2. Cybersquatting: Avoid registering domain names with the intention of selling them to trademark holders at inflated prices.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">3. Domain Name Dispute Resolution: Understand the dispute resolution processes and procedures for domain name conflicts.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Conclusion</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">AI domain name investing can be a lucrative opportunity, but it&rsquo;s crucial to be aware of the potential pitfalls and scams. By understanding common fraudulent schemes, taking necessary precautions, and being mindful of legal considerations, investors can protect themselves from financial losses and navigate the complex world of AI domain name investing safely. Remember, always prioritize caution and thorough research to avoid falling victim to the dark side of AI domain name investing.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Starting a New Marijuana Business? You&rsquo;ll Need a Good Domain Name for That!</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">You can view handpicked domain names at the number one platform for marijuana domain names&nbsp;<a href="http://www.marijuanadomain.store/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">here</a>.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*WoGrM10oubWExo35', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Investing'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Jack Black')),
	(UUID(), 'Investing in Steep.', 'Steep is revolutionizing Business Intelligence (BI) by addressing the modern data stacks unmet needs through a user-centric, metrics-first approach. Founded by Johan (former Head of Analytics at Spotify, Izettle, and Kry) and Nino (ex-Chief Design Officer at Izettle), Steep simplifies data accessibility for non-technical users while empowering teams with real data governance and enhanced collaboration. Leveraging a semantic layer architecture, Steep integrates AI-driven features like report generation and conversational queries, setting it apart from legacy BI tools like Tableau and Microsoft Power BI. Backed by a $4M seed round led by Connect, Steep is poised to become the leader in modern BI innovation.', '<h1 data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Revolutionizing Business Intelligence for the Modern Data Stack</strong></h1><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 1400w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-testid="og" /><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png" alt="" width="700" height="529" /></picture></div></div></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Two product founders, obsessed with user-centricity.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">A giant market category dominated by unloved old products.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">A core technology shift in the data infrastructure.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">BI is the only layer in the new modern stack without a new multi-billion leader and&nbsp;<a href="https://steep.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Steep</a>&nbsp;is building the product to win it.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">We at Connect are thrilled to partner with Johan and Nino, leading a $4m seed round along with existing investor Inventure, and participation from Alliance VC, Antler, and Greens.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Johan and Nino are redefining BI with an opinionated point of view and a fresh perspective. They are insiders with an outsider&rsquo;s point of view. Johan, is the former Head of Analytics at Spotify, Izettle, and Kry, and Nino is the ex-Chief Design Officer at Izettle. They repeatedly saw overworked data teams and unhappy end users who can&rsquo;t consistently get what they need. Together they combine deep market understanding with a zeal for user-centric design.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Central to Steep&rsquo;s philosophy is an unwavering obsession with user-centricity. Steep core product opinion is to be metrics-first. This means that even non-technical users can get insights effortlessly as they create and manipulate data work without heavy reliance on technical teams. Steep truly changes how companies use data together. It &ldquo;makes sense &hellip;common&rdquo; 😍</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Companies like VOI love Steep.&nbsp;<em>Steep has made a big impact at Voi by truly enabling all users to find and analyze data themselves with much lower dependency on data teams.&rdquo; &mdash;&nbsp;</em>Magnus Dahlb&auml;ck &mdash; Senior Director Data &amp; Platform at VOI</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Steep product advantage starts with its native architecture built for the semantic layer, which enables real data governance and accessibility, which are the two current unsolved pains. The semantic layer is also the optimal data structure for integrating generative AI for report generation and conversational query capabilities, setting Steep ahead for AI powered automation.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The BI market is currently dominated by legacy giants such as Tableau, Looker, and Microsoft Power BI. Expensive and with poor user experience, they struggle to keep pace with the evolving demands of the modern data stack. BI is the only layer in the new modern stack without a new multi-billion leader and we believe Steep is building the product to win it.</p>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*sSPgYmiJvo7ek1pMzP_T6w.png', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Investing'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Jack Black')),
	(UUID(), 'Joining Forces with Roofstock and ForumPay to Simplify Real Estate Investing', 'Landshare partnership with Roofstock and ForumPay revolutionizes real estate investing by enabling stablecoin holders to directly access and tokenize properties without relying on traditional banking systems. This collaboration simplifies property acquisition, tapping into the $14+ million single-family rental market and democratizing investments with fractional ownership starting at $1. By integrating stablecoin payments, Landshare streamlines transactions, reduces financial intermediaries, and aligns with the $5 trillion tokenized real estate market opportunity. This initiative strengthens Landshares mission to connect crypto assets with real-world investments, positioning it as a leader in transforming real estate through blockchain.', '<div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph="">At Landshare, we&rsquo;re always seeking ways to make real estate investing more accessible, efficient, and connected to the blockchain world. Our latest partnership with Roofstock and ForumPay marks a significant milestone, simplifying the acquisition and tokenization of real estate properties for our community.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">A Direct Path from Stablecoins to Real Estate</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">This collaboration enables stablecoin investors to access Roofstock&rsquo;s extensive property inventory without converting their assets to fiat or relying on traditional banking systems. Thanks to ForumPay&rsquo;s stablecoin payment integration, Landshare can now seamlessly purchase and tokenize properties.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">By tapping into the&nbsp;<strong>$14+ million US single-family rental (SFR) market</strong>, this partnership offers substantial growth potential for investors. Once tokenized, these real estate assets breathe new life into an otherwise illiquid sector, making real estate investments accessible to everyone. Through Landshare, users can invest in fractional property ownership starting&nbsp;<strong>from as little as $1</strong>&nbsp;&mdash; breaking down barriers for everyday investors.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">Why This Matters</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Integrating stablecoin payments into real estate is a game-changer. It streamlines property purchases, reduces reliance on traditional financial intermediaries, and provides our community with more flexibility. Given that the tokenized real estate market is&nbsp;<strong>projected to become a $5 trillion opportunity</strong>, Landshare is well-positioned to capitalize on this emerging trend, offering unparalleled access to a vast and growing market.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Jordan Friske, CEO of Landshare, shared his enthusiasm:</strong></p><blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><em>&ldquo;</em>This partnership is a significant step for Landshare. It simplifies scaling efforts by creating a direct connection between stablecoin investments and tokenized properties. We believe this integration will improve efficiency and benefit our growing community of investors.<em>&rdquo;</em></p></blockquote><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">Looking Ahead</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">This partnership helps us further connect crypto holders with real-world assets, delivering practical blockchain solutions for real estate investment. Our collaboration with Roofstock and ForumPay is a key milestone for&nbsp;<a href="https://medium.com/@landshare/feature-preview-landshare-tokenization-hub-ca2e3ec3eb48" rel="noopener"><strong>Landshare&rsquo;s Tokenization Hub</strong></a>, making property onboarding easier and pushing forward our mission to transform real estate investing.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">About Our Partners</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">👉&nbsp;<a href="https://www.roofstock.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><strong>Roofstock</strong></a>&nbsp;is a leading online marketplace for real estate investments, facilitating over $3 billion in acquisitions since its launch in 2015. They&rsquo;ve managed 25,000+ homes and are known for making real estate accessible to a global audience.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">👉&nbsp;<a href="https://forumpay.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow"><strong>ForumPay</strong></a>&nbsp;provides seamless cryptocurrency payment solutions, enabling individuals and businesses to transact with digital currencies in real-world scenarios.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Together, we&rsquo;re shaping the future of real estate investment. Stay tuned for more exciting developments!</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">🔗&nbsp;<a href="https://app.landshare.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Explore Landshare&rsquo;s App</a></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*nsxNnWikMm3Tg31RKJ1AQg.png', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Investing'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Ivy White')),
	(UUID(), 'Investing in STARs: My Reflections on MacKenzie Scott''s Milestone Gift to Opportunity@Work', 'Opportunity@Work has received a transformative $20 million grant from MacKenzie Scotts Yield Giving to advance its mission of creating a skills-first labor market for the 70 million STARs (Skilled Through Alternative Routes) in the U.S. STARs possess valuable skills gained outside traditional education but face systemic barriers to upward mobility due to degree-based hiring practices. This grant will empower Opportunity@Work to enhance STARs hiring practices, integrate skills-based data into talent platforms, and build regional and industry networks that prioritize skills over credentials. By tearing the "paper ceiling," this initiative aims to unlock STARs economic potential, fostering inclusive growth across communities.', '<p><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*sb8jU1Xy9NOihlcGFaPZlQ.png" alt="" /></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph="">When I co-founded Opportunity@Work 7 years ago, we saw many signs of a disconnect in the U.S. labor market. Across the country, I&rsquo;d heard from hundreds of employers that they &ldquo;can&rsquo;t find the talent we need.&rdquo; Yet at the same time, over and over, I heard from people working in those same communities, saying: &ldquo;I know what I can do, but no one will give me a chance.&rdquo;</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">We listened to what we heard, we learned from many promising initiatives, community leaders, industry innovators, and we dug deep into the data on how Americans from every background gain skills, build careers, and earn more. We tested, succeeded or failed, and built new insights.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/byronauguste/2019/02/07/low-wage-not-low-skill-why-devaluing-our-workers-matters/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Low-wage is not low-skill</a>: millions of low-wage workers have skills today for middle-wage jobs.&nbsp;<a href="https://www.cnn.com/2022/10/13/perspectives/college-degrees-careers-roslansky-auguste/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Skills are the currency of the labor market</a>, mostly gained on the job. Our economy needs skills, and&nbsp;<a href="https://opportunityatwork.org/stars/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">70 million American workers are STARs</a>: &lsquo;skilled through alternative routes&rsquo;. STARs have valuable skills, but not bachelor&rsquo;s degrees. &ldquo;Screening out&rdquo; skilled workers without degrees from upwardly mobile jobs leaves STARs talent undervalued in&nbsp;<a href="https://opportunityatwork.org/our-solutions/stars-insights/look-to-the-stars/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">regions and industries less dynamic</a>, and reduces opportunities for veterans, communities of color, and in rural America. It hurts us all.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Fast-forward to today, Opportunity@Work is grateful to announce that we&rsquo;ve received&nbsp;<a href="https://opportunityatwork.org/press-release/opportunitywork-receives-20-million-from-mackenzie-scott/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">a grant of $20 million from Yield Giving</a>, the groundbreaking philanthropy founded by MacKenzie Scott.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">This remarkable investment and generous gift affirms the vital role STARs play in building our economy. It recognizes Opportunity@Work&rsquo;s work to build awareness of STARs as a category of talent, insights to spark action by employers and policymakers, and launch a movement to&nbsp;<a href="https://www.tearthepaperceiling.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Tear the Paper Ceiling</a>. It brings us closer to fulfilling our mission of building a skills-first labor market that works for STARs &mdash; one where &ldquo;if you can do the job, you can get the job&rdquo;.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Personally, I&rsquo;m proud of what Opportunity@Work has accomplished and I&rsquo;m grateful to the hundreds of organizations who are our essential partners &mdash; businesses and&nbsp;<a href="https://opportunityatwork.org/enterprises/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">industry leaders</a>, educators and&nbsp;<a href="https://www.tearthepaperceiling.org/meet-our-partners" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">workforce institutions</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://opportunityatwork.org/stars-policy-project/public-sector-hub/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">state and local governments</a>, policymakers, tech innovators, investors and philanthropists, community and labor organizations, STARs&nbsp;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/lashanalewis_tearthepaperceiling-hirestars-activity-7184325202640580608-P-FX/?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">leading</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/kennynguyen1_tearthepaperceiling-hirestars-activity-7184211096348626944-M3ig/?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">showing</a>&nbsp;the way.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">MacKenzie Scott&rsquo;s Yield Giving joins other&nbsp;<a href="https://opportunityatwork.org/philanthropies/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">philanthropic</a>&nbsp;partners to invest in STARs hiring and economic mobility. Opportunity@Work will deploy and leverage this investment over the next four years to:</p><ul><li data-selectable-paragraph="">Equip industry and public sector employers to hire STARs into good, in-demand jobs;</li><li data-selectable-paragraph="">Shift employer behavior to include the STARs talent in regional and industry networks;</li><li data-selectable-paragraph="">Integrate STARs skills and &lsquo;screen-in signal&rsquo; data into talent technology platforms and offer onramps for a wide range of STARs-serving networks to mainstream STARs hiring.</li></ul><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Watch this space. During the next 6 months, Opportunity@Work will work closely with partners to develop a nationwide initiative (launching January 2025, TBD) that enlists regional, industry, technology, and civic institutions to&nbsp;<a href="https://opportunityatwork.org/our-solutions/stars-insights/barriers-and-breakthroughs-report/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">remove barriers and unlock breakthroughs</a>&nbsp;for STARs economic contribution and mobility. Work is solving problems; STARs are problem solvers. We&rsquo;ll need all our talents in the years ahead. We need to&nbsp;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7077749951572701184?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">change assumptions, business practices, and public policies</a>&nbsp;to rewire the labor market to value everyone&rsquo;s skills, however those skills are gained. This problem was created in divided silos, sometimes by accident. We&rsquo;ll solve the problem together, on purpose.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">You can learn more at&nbsp;<a href="http://opportunityatwork.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">opportunityatwork.org</a>.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>' , 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*sb8jU1Xy9NOihlcGFaPZlQ.png', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Investing'), FALSE, 89, '2024-02-01 14:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Ivy White')),
    (UUID(), 'Why I''m not investing in AI?', 'In May 2023, despite the surging interest in generative AI (gen AI) startups, I refrained from investing in the sector, citing four key concerns: rapid technological advancement potentially overshadowing current startups, reliance on dominant AI models like GPT-4 without unique competitive advantages, intense competition within the nascent market, and uncertainties about timing and long-term impact. Instead, I focused on startups leveraging AI as a tool to enhance efficiency, reduce costs, and scale rapidly with minimal resources. While I have since started investing in select AI startups as of April 2024, this article reflects my reasoning during an earlier stage of market development.','<p><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*0Zj7ZhI9_SVzXPSVeJOYxA.png" alt="" /></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph="">[EDIT] : This article dates back from May 2023. One year later (April 2024), I have carefully started investing in a few AI startups. I believe timing is now better. I&rsquo;ll leave this article up so that you see my reasoning at the time.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Unless you&rsquo;ve been living under a rock for the last few months, you&rsquo;ve probably seen the tidal wave that is AI. You&rsquo;ve used Generative AI.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">You&rsquo;ve also probably heard everywhere that this is the next big revolution. Bill Gates says it&rsquo;s as big as computers or the Internet.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Investors are rushing in. It&rsquo;s supposedly the next big thing, you can&rsquo;t miss it! However, I&rsquo;m not investing in AI.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Why ? Let&rsquo;s explore together.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">I attended&nbsp;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/school/y-combinator/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Y Combinator</a>&rsquo;s latest Demo Day in early April 2023, as I do twice a year every year, and noticed that 75% of YC startups this year are what we call &ldquo;gen AI&rdquo; (for generative AI). My focus being on Y Combinator startups, I should have been all over this, however many things kept me from doing it.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">My first doubt is around the speed of development of the technology. Most of those startups are using GPT4 (since&nbsp;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sam-altman-4384094/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Sam Altman</a>, the founder of both&nbsp;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/openai/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">OpenAI</a>&nbsp;and Y Combinator supposedly gave all YC startups free access). But GPT5 is coming at the end of 2023. What&rsquo;s to say that the new AI won&rsquo;t have all those functionalities internally? Maybe allowing all these startups to use their tool is just market research. The AI is already so smart and so versatile that it&rsquo;s easy to imagine new functions being added to the newest version. What happens to all those startups when ChatGPT 5 does the same thing natively, for free, and already has 100 million users?</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">My second doubt is related to the first. The real value in all of those startups come from the AI model behind them. 99% of the time it&rsquo;s ChatGPT, but these startups will reassure you: we can switch to another AI if necessary. That&rsquo;s not reassuring at all. If the value you create comes from OpenAI, I want to invest in OpenAI. Sadly, this is no longer a seed startup and they&rsquo;re not really looking for investors with&nbsp;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/microsoft/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Microsoft</a>&nbsp;injecting $10b in the company in January 2023.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">My third doubt is around competition. This AI thing is a literal gold rush. Tens, even hundreds of startups are all going after the exact same thing at the exact same time. Including inside YC&rsquo;s same cohort. There was some topics where 10 different startup just in this batch where competing. This is unheard of, at this magnitude. Who&rsquo;s going to win? It&rsquo;s almost impossible to predict. It&rsquo;s such a new market with many moving parts. Don&rsquo;t get me wrong, you could ask this question about any startup in any market, and it&rsquo;s my job as an investor to only back the companies that will crush their competition. I call this the &ldquo;unfair advantage&rdquo; criteria: what does the startup has that no one else has and that no one else will ever be able to get (hence the &ldquo;unfair&rdquo;)? In the case of gen AI startups, their only advantage is access to ChatGPT, that basically anyone can get. So, what&rsquo;s the unfair advantage? Most of the time I couldn&rsquo;t answer this question. So I didn&rsquo;t invest.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Finally, my fourth and last doubt is about timing. All of this is so new. Will AI be the revolution we were promised? I honestly think that yes, in a way, it will, but me thinking it doesn&rsquo;t make it true. I can be wrong, and we can all be collectively be wrong. Remember crypto ? Everyone said it would revolutionize financial markets. Well, so far, it hasn&rsquo;t. Maybe it will, but we&rsquo;ll have to wait and see. Same thing applies for AI. Will this take many more years than we think? Worse, will this flop? It&rsquo;s still possible.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Even if this ends up being the revolution we&rsquo;ve been advertised, the first movers aren&rsquo;t always the big winners. You&rsquo;ve read countless times that&nbsp;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/google/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Google</a>&nbsp;was the 14th search engine and Facebook (<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/meta/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Meta</a>) the 10th social network (numbers are debated but you get the idea). So will the startups from 2023 be the big winners of tomorrow? Or do we have to wait a few months / years for the space to mature? It&rsquo;s impossible to predict.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">So what am I doing instead?</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">I&rsquo;m investing in startups that are using AI in their day to day work to go faster, to save money with less employees being able to do more work and to be more productive. AI gives these startup a better leverage to grow even faster.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/chamath/" target="_blank" rel="noopener ugc nofollow">Chamath Palihapitiya</a>&nbsp;says AI will create startups able to win big with little funding and few people. His conclusion is that seed investing is what makes the most sense right now, because those startups might never need to raise a series A, B, etc. with their lean organisation, thanks to AI. Good news: I&rsquo;m focusing on seed investing as I&rsquo;ve been doing for the last 10 years.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>','https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:4800/format:webp/1*0Zj7ZhI9_SVzXPSVeJOYxA.png', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Investing'), FALSE, 89, '2024-02-01 14:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Jack Black')),  
    (UUID(), 'Unleash Your Money: The Personal Finance Revolution', 'Personal finance is more than numbers—its a journey toward freedom and fulfillment. This guide invites readers to transform their money mindset in just 30 days, focusing on budgeting, saving, and smart spending. It emphasizes balance, aligning financial decisions with personal values, and embracing change as a path to empowerment. Through actionable steps and an emphasis on progress over perfection, the article encourages readers to take control of their finances and build a life of experiences, security, and purpose.', ' <div><p><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*c9RikxKcCA0bGNV_" alt="" /></p></div><div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><mark>Day 1 of 30 to transform your personal finances. To read all about the upcoming schedule and what to expect please check out my article describing the goals and schedule.</mark></p><div><div><div><h2>Unlock Your Financial Freedom in 30 Days: A Guide to Transforming Your Money Mindset</h2><div><h3>Transform Your Finances in Just One Month: The Ultimate Guide to Gaining Control and Building Wealth</h3></div><div><p>medium.com</p></div></div></div></div><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><mark>Ever felt like your money just vanishes? One moment it&rsquo;s snug in your account, the next &mdash; vanished, leaving you puzzled about its quick escape</mark>. It&rsquo;s time to take control and show your money who&rsquo;s in charge. Personal finance isn&rsquo;t merely about pinching pennies or constantly checking your bank app. It&rsquo;s about designing a life filled with enriching experiences without the burden of financial worries.&nbsp;<mark>It&rsquo;s about putting your money to work for you, allowing for relaxation and enjoyment of life&rsquo;s journey.</mark></p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">Beyond Numbers</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Recall the days when budgets and savings seemed dull? I&rsquo;ve been there. But here&rsquo;s a secret: mastering personal finance feels like unlocking a superpower you didn&rsquo;t realize you possessed.<mark>&nbsp;It&rsquo;s the ability to turn your dreams into reality, one wise decision at a time.</mark></p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">Embrace the Essentials</h1><ul><li data-selectable-paragraph=""><mark><strong>Budgeting</strong></mark><mark>:&nbsp;</mark>View it as your financial compass. It&rsquo;s less about restriction and more about understanding your money&rsquo;s flow and making conscious choices. Yes, you can still enjoy coffee outings with friends. It&rsquo;s about balance, not deprivation.</li><li data-selectable-paragraph=""><mark><strong>Saving</strong></mark><mark>:</mark>&nbsp;Consider this both your safety net and your launch pad. Whether it&rsquo;s for emergency purposes or saving up for that dream getaway, setting aside money grants you freedom and serenity. It&rsquo;s okay to start small, but the key is to start.</li><li data-selectable-paragraph=""><mark><strong>Smart Spending</strong></mark><mark>:&nbsp;</mark>Each dollar you spend represents a decision. Will you invest in experiences that enrich your life or in items that merely fill your space? Spending wisely means aligning your expenditures with your values and ambitions.</li></ul><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">The Heart of the Matter</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Personal finance is inherently personal. It&rsquo;s your gate pass to the lifestyle you&rsquo;ve always coveted but thought was out of reach. Dream of globetrotting? Launching your own venture? Early retirement? It&rsquo;s all achievable, provided you appreciate the influence of your financial decisions.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph="">Dare to Change</h1><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><mark>Change can indeed be intimidating.</mark>&nbsp;But what if taking charge of your financial health is one of the most empowering steps you could take? Imagine a life where money ceases to be a stressor but instead becomes a tool for crafting happiness and fulfillment.</p><h1 data-selectable-paragraph=""><mark>Begin Your Journey</mark></h1><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><mark>This is your call to action.</mark>&nbsp;An invitation to the personal finance revolution. It&rsquo;s not about flawlessness. It&rsquo;s about progress, learning from missteps, and celebrating every victory, no matter its size. Each step forward brings you nearer to the life you desire.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><mark>It&rsquo;s time to secure your financial future and live by your own rules.</mark>&nbsp;Because ultimately, it&rsquo;s not just about the money &mdash; it&rsquo;s about what the money enables you to do. Ready to put your money to work? Your adventure is just beginning.</p></div></div></div></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*c9RikxKcCA0bGNV_', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Personal Finance'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Kathy Moore')),
    (UUID(), 'Personal Finance Planning for the Second Quarter of the Year', 'The second quarter of the year is a pivotal time to reassess and refine your personal finance goals. This period offers the opportunity to review budgets, set SMART financial objectives, reduce high-interest debt, boost savings, rebalance investments, and optimize tax efficiency. By taking proactive steps now, you can adjust your financial course and make significant progress toward long-term success. Stay focused and make this quarter a turning point in achieving financial stability and growth.', '<p><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*49RK7v8GUA-aOSRZVcAAcA.jpeg" alt="" /></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph="">With the first quarter of the year behind us, it&rsquo;s an ideal time to reflect on our financial goals and make necessary adjustments to our plans. The second quarter of the year is a crucial period to get back on track or to accelerate your personal finance planning. Whether you&rsquo;re saving for a big purchase, trying to reduce debt, or investing for the future, a mid-year check-in can help ensure you&rsquo;re on the right path. Here are some strategies to make the most out of the second quarter for your financial well-being.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Review and Adjust Your Budget</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">The foundation of personal finance planning is a solid budget. Take time to review your budget from the first quarter. Compare your actual spending against planned expenses, and identify areas where you can cut back or need to allocate more resources. Adjustments may be necessary due to changes in income, unexpected expenses, or shifting priorities.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Set Specific Financial Goals</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">If you haven&rsquo;t already, now is the time to set specific, measurable, achievable, relevant, and time-bound (SMART) financial goals for the remainder of the year. Whether it&rsquo;s reducing debt by a certain amount, saving for a vacation, or increasing your emergency fund, having clear goals will help guide your financial decisions.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Focus on Reducing Debt</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">High interest debt, especially from credit cards, can hinder your financial progress. Use the second quarter to focus on strategies for debt reduction, such as the debt avalanche or debt snowball methods. Consider consolidating debts or refinancing to lower interest rates if possible.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Increase Your Savings</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Evaluate your savings goals and consider increasing your contributions, especially to your emergency fund and retirement accounts. Even a small increase can compound over time, significantly impacting your financial future. Take advantage of any tax-advantaged accounts like IRAs or 401(k)s.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Rebalance Your Investment Portfolio</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Market fluctuations can alter the allocation of your investment portfolio away from your original goals. Review and rebalance your portfolio to ensure it aligns with your risk tolerance and investment objectives. Diversification remains key to managing risk effectively.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Plan for Tax Efficiency</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Consider tax implications in your financial planning. Look for opportunities to minimize taxes through retirement contributions, health savings accounts, or charitable donations. Planning ahead can save you money when tax season arrives.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">By taking these steps in the second quarter, you&rsquo;re not only adjusting your course but also proactively steering towards your financial goals. Regular check-ins and adjustments to your financial plan can make a significant difference in achieving long-term success. Stay informed, stay motivated, and make this quarter the turning point in your personal finance journey.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*49RK7v8GUA-aOSRZVcAAcA.jpeg', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Personal Finance'), FALSE, 89, '2024-02-01 14:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Kathy Moore')),
    (UUID(), 'Finances: Exploring Types of Personal Finance and Why It''s So Important', 'Understanding personal finance is essential for achieving financial stability, empowering informed decisions, and building a secure future. This article explores various aspects of personal finance, including budgeting, saving, investing, debt management, and tax planning, while highlighting their importance in shaping financial success. Mastering these concepts enables individuals to adapt to changing financial landscapes, achieve goals, and leave a legacy of financial literacy. By embracing financial education, anyone can transform their dreams into reality and secure a prosperous future.', '<p><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:568/1*Mf6uGfMbz0hz6Q1VY-1iFg.jpeg" alt="" /></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>**Introduction:**</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">There, are some fellow financial aficionados! Are you ready to embark on an epic journey through the fascinating realm of personal finance? Buckle up because we&rsquo;re about to dive deep into not just one, not two, but types of personal finance, uncovering why each of them is an essential piece of the financial puzzle. Whether you&rsquo;re a seasoned money maestro or just dipping your toes into the waters of financial literacy, this blog is your ultimate guide to understanding the importance of personal finance and how it impacts every aspect of your life. So, grab your favorite snack, get cozy, and let&rsquo;s embark on this enlightening adventure together!</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>**Importance:**</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Now, you might be wondering, &ldquo;Why bother learning about all these different aspects of personal finance?&rdquo; Well, let me tell you &mdash; understanding personal finance isn&rsquo;t just about balancing your checkbook or saving for a rainy day. It&rsquo;s about taking control of your financial future, empowering yourself to make informed decisions, and ultimately, living the life you&rsquo;ve always dreamed of. Here&rsquo;s why it&rsquo;s so darn important:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">First and foremost, knowledge is power, especially when it comes to your finances. By familiarizing yourself with the ins and outs of personal finance, you gain the confidence to navigate complex financial decisions, from budgeting and investing to retirement planning and beyond.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Financial stability is another crucial aspect. By mastering personal finance concepts, you build a solid foundation that can weather life&rsquo;s inevitable storms. Whether it&rsquo;s unexpected expenses, job loss, or economic downturns, you&rsquo;ll be better equipped to handle whatever comes your way.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">But it&rsquo;s not just about weathering the storms &mdash; it&rsquo;s also about setting sail towards your goals. Whether you dream of buying a home, starting a business, traveling the world, or retiring early, understanding personal finance principles helps you turn those dreams into achievable goals.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Adaptability is key in today&rsquo;s ever-changing world, and personal finance is no exception. The financial landscape is constantly evolving, from new investment opportunities to changes in tax laws and economic trends. By staying informed and adaptable, you can seize opportunities, navigate challenges, and thrive in any financial climate.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Last but certainly not least, there&rsquo;s the legacy factor. Beyond your financial well-being, understanding personal finance allows you to pass on valuable knowledge and resources to future generations. Whether it&rsquo;s teaching your children about the importance of saving or leaving a charitable legacy, you have the power to shape a brighter financial future for those who come after you.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Hey there, savvy savers and financial enthusiasts! Welcome back to our cozy corner of the internet where we&rsquo;re diving deep into the fascinating world of personal finance. Today, we&rsquo;re embarking on an exciting journey as we explore not just one, not two, but 101 types of personal finance and uncover why every one of them is crucial for your financial well-being. So, grab your favorite beverage, get comfy, and let&rsquo;s get started!</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">1. Budgeting: Ah, the cornerstone of personal finance. Creating and sticking to a budget helps you track your spending, prioritize your expenses, and ultimately, reach your financial goals.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">2. Emergency Fund: Life is unpredictable, but having an emergency fund cushions the blow when unexpected expenses arise, like car repairs or medical bills.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">3. Savings Accounts: Whether it&rsquo;s a traditional savings account or a high-yield one, having a designated place to stash your cash for short-term goals is key.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">4. Retirement Savings: It&rsquo;s never too early to start thinking about retirement. Building a nest egg through IRAs, 401(k)s, or other retirement accounts ensures you can enjoy your golden years without financial stress.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">5. Investing Basics: Understanding the fundamentals of investing &mdash; from stocks and bonds to mutual funds and ETFs &mdash; empowers you to grow your wealth over time.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">6. Asset Allocation: Diversifying your investments across different asset classes helps manage risk and optimize returns based on your risk tolerance and financial goals.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">7. Compound Interest: The eighth wonder of the world, as Einstein famously said. Harnessing the power of compound interest by reinvesting earnings can turbocharge your savings and investments.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">8. Credit Scores: Your credit score is your financial report card. Monitoring and maintaining a good credit score opens doors to better loan rates, credit card offers, and more.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">9. Debt Management: From student loans to credit card debt, learning how to effectively manage and pay off debt is crucial for achieving financial freedom.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">10. Insurance: Protecting yourself and your assets with the right insurance coverage &mdash; whether it&rsquo;s health, life, auto, or home insurance &mdash; provides peace of mind against life&rsquo;s uncertainties.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">11. Tax Planning: Understanding the tax implications of your financial decisions can help minimize your tax burden and maximize your savings.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">12. Estate Planning: Ensuring your assets are distributed according to your wishes and minimizing estate taxes requires careful estate planning.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">13. Financial Independence: Achieving financial independence means having enough passive income to cover your expenses, giving you the freedom to live life on your terms.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">14. Frugal Living: Adopting frugal habits like meal planning, DIY projects, and shopping smartly helps stretch your dollars further and live within your means.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">15. Side Hustles: Diversifying your income streams through side hustles or freelancing gigs can accelerate your journey toward financial goals.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">16. Real Estate: Whether it&rsquo;s owning your home, investing in rental properties, or flipping houses, real estate can be a lucrative avenue for building wealth.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">17. Financial Literacy: Continuously educating yourself about personal finance topics ensures you make informed decisions and stay on top of your financial game.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">18. Charitable Giving: Giving back to your community not only makes a positive impact but also provides tax benefits and a sense of fulfillment.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">19. Entrepreneurship: Starting and growing your own business can be a rewarding path towards financial success and independence.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">20. Health Savings Accounts (HSAs): Using HSAs to save for medical expenses tax-free can help offset the rising costs of healthcare.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Phew! That&rsquo;s just the tip of the iceberg when it comes to personal finance topics. As you can see, there&rsquo;s a whole world of financial knowledge waiting to be explored, and each aspect plays a vital role in shaping your financial future.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">But why is understanding these types of personal finance so important? Well, let&rsquo;s break it down:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">1. Empowerment: Knowledge is power, especially when it comes to your finances. Understanding these topics empowers you to take control of your financial destiny and make informed decisions.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">2. Financial Stability: By mastering these concepts, you can build a solid financial foundation that withstands life&rsquo;s ups and downs, providing stability and security for you and your loved ones.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">3. Goal Achievement: Whether your goal is to buy a house, travel the world, or retire early, having a strong grasp of personal finance principles helps you turn your dreams into achievable goals.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">4. Adaptability: The financial landscape is constantly evolving, but armed with knowledge, you can adapt to changes, seize opportunities, and navigate challenges with confidence.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">5. Legacy Building: Beyond your financial well-being, understanding personal finance allows you to pass on valuable knowledge and resources to future generations, leaving a lasting legacy of financial literacy and prosperity.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>**Conclusion:**</strong></p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">So there you have it &mdash; a glimpse into the vast and vital world of personal finance. From budgeting and investing to retirement planning and beyond, each aspect plays a crucial role in shaping your financial future. By embracing financial literacy, you empower yourself to take control of your finances, achieve your goals, and build a legacy of prosperity for generations to come. So, whether you&rsquo;re just starting your financial journey or looking to level up your money game, remember this: knowledge is the key to financial success. Keep learning, keep growing, and watch your dreams transform into reality. Here&rsquo;s to a future filled with financial abundance, freedom, and fulfillment. Cheers to your financial journey &mdash; may it be as rewarding as it is enlightening!</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">So, there you have it, folks &mdash; a whirlwind tour of types of personal finance and why they&rsquo;re so darn important. Remember, Rome wasn&rsquo;t built in a day, and neither is financial mastery. Take it one step at a time, keep learning, and before you know it, you&rsquo;ll be a bonafide financial guru!</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Until next time, stay curious, stay financially savvy, and stay fabulous! Happy budgeting!</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*Mf6uGfMbz0hz6Q1VY-1iFg.jpeg', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Personal Finance'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Kathy Moore')),
    (UUID(), 'From Niche Selection to Profit: Building a Successful Personal Finance Blog', 'Building a successful personal finance blog that generates passive income requires a combination of strategic planning, high-quality content creation, and audience engagement. This article explores the critical steps involved, starting with niche selection to target a specific audience, followed by producing insightful and engaging content to establish credibility. Effective use of SEO and marketing enhances visibility, while diverse monetization strategies, including affiliate marketing and sponsored content, help maximize revenue. Cultivating a loyal audience and leveraging automation tools streamline growth and scalability. Continuous learning ensures relevance in the ever-evolving financial landscape. With dedication and persistence, personal finance blogging can become a valuable platform for financial education and a reliable income source.','<div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Many individuals find the proposition of generating passive income through personal finance blogging quite attractive: this approach marries a passion for personal finance with potential financial gain.</p><figure><div tabindex="0"><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 1400w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-testid="og" /><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg" alt="" width="700" height="400" /></picture></div></div><figcaption data-selectable-paragraph="">From Niche Selection to Profit: Building a Successful Personal Finance Blog</figcaption></figure><p data-selectable-paragraph="">In our exploration below, we dig into strategies &mdash; alongside critical considerations &mdash; for constructing an effective blog on personal finances; one that generates income passively.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">1. Identifying Your Niche</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">For your blog&rsquo;s success, it is critical that you select a specific niche within the vast personal finance category. Focus on an exclusive aspect like debt reduction, early retirement strategies, or beginner&rsquo;s investing to attract a target audience seeking guidance in these areas. Choosing a well-defined niche empowers you as an expert in that field and enables tailored advice and solutions to meet your readers&rsquo; unique needs. Building a loyal readership and positioning your blog as a go-to resource for specific financial guidance hinges on this specificity.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">2. Creating Quality Content</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Any successful blog hinges on the foundation of its content. In personal finance blogging, one must prioritize delivering insightful, accurate, and engaging content. Your material ought to equip readers with the ability to make informed financial decisions; this can be achieved through detailed guides, thought-provoking analyses &mdash; even inspiring success stories. Your blog&rsquo;s credibility and authority in the personal finance niche will establish itself when you produce high-quality content that resonates with your audience; this will not only attract new readers but also encourage shares.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">3. SEO and Marketing</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Enhancing your blog&rsquo;s visibility and attracting organic traffic require essential tools such as Search Engine Optimization (SEO) and marketing. Effective SEO strategies: using relevant keywords; optimizing the structure of your website; and creating content that caters to audience search queries &mdash; all play a pivotal role in this process. In parallel, marketing efforts &mdash; notably social media engagement along with email campaigns &mdash; act not only as an active promotion for your blog but also foster community around your brand: they are indispensable complements to successful SEO implementation. Together, these strategies enhance your online presence and draw more readers to your site.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">4. Monetization Strategies</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">You can monetize your personal finance blog through a variety of channels: Affiliate marketing offers the opportunity to earn commissions by promoting niche-relevant financial products or services; display advertising, on the other hand, generates revenue based on either ad views or clicks within your site. Partnering with financial institutions to create paid posts &mdash; that&rsquo;s what sponsored content involves; on the other hand, direct income can be generated by selling your own products or services: think of it as offering a menu featuring offerings like financial planning consultations and online courses. Each strategy presents distinct advantages &mdash; tailor them accordingly for an audience specific to your blog&rsquo;s focus and tone.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">5. Building an Audience</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Your personal finance blog&rsquo;s success hinges on how well you cultivate and maintain a dedicated audience. Key strategies for building an audience include: engaging with your readers through regular, valuable content updates; responding to comments; and interacting on social media platforms. Fostering loyalty and trust &mdash; crucial for retaining visitors and encouraging word-of-mouth recommendations &mdash; requires you to establish a personal connection with your readership. A vibrant and committed audience propels the growth of your blog: it not only boosts traffic but also amplifies opportunities for monetization.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">6. Automation and Scaling</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">As your personal finance blog expands, you must automate repetitive tasks and scale content production; these actions are vital. Utilizing tools for scheduling social media posts, automating email newsletters &mdash; even managing content calendars &mdash; can prove time-saving. Consider the option of employing freelance writers or virtual assistants: this strategy not only amplifies your operations but also permits a focus on strategic growth initiatives and high-value activities. You can achieve sustained growth by leveraging automation and delegation, which enable a consistent content output and effective audience engagement.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">7. Continuous Learning and Adaptation</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">New trends, products, and regulations continuously emerge in the dynamic financial world. To guarantee your content&rsquo;s relevance and value to readers &mdash; staying informed and adaptable is essential. By pursuing continuous learning via industry news, financial publications, and professional development courses; you proactively position yourself ahead of the curve. Maintaining your blog&rsquo;s authority and relevance in the constantly shifting personal finance landscape necessitates adapting your content strategy: it must reflect not only the latest financial insights but also reader interests.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Conclusion</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">A combination of strategic planning, hard work, and persistence is necessary to generate passive income from personal finance blogging. Focus on creating valuable content; optimize for SEO; and implement effective monetization strategies &mdash; all while engaging with your audience: these steps will pave the way towards building a successful blog that enhances people&rsquo;s financial management and yields you steady passive income. Always remember this &mdash; success does not occur overnight. It&rsquo;s a gradual process that requires patience, dedication, and continuous learning.</p></div></div></div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><strong>Wait a second</strong>.&nbsp;<em>You should get my articles in your inbox.&nbsp;</em><a href="https://medium.com/@petefacty/subscribe" rel="noopener"><strong><em>Subscribe here</em></strong></a><em>.</em></p><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><em>If you want to start writing on Medium yourself and earn money passively you only need a membership for $5 a month. If you sign up&nbsp;</em><a href="https://petefacty.medium.com/membership" rel="noopener"><strong><em>with my link</em></strong></a><em>, you support me with a part of your fee without additional costs.</em></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 'https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*6YFMmLLYeA0OozTg', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Personal Finance'), FALSE, 89, '2024-02-01 14:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Leo Martinez')),
    (UUID(), '5 Personal Finance Tips to Become Financially Free in 2024', 'Achieving financial freedom requires mastering core personal finance principles and progressing through three levels of financial stability: debt-free living, affording significant assets, and long-term abundance. This article outlines five essential tips to guide readers toward financial independence in 2024.','<div><p><img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*laLVZh5bQCROaDB-" alt="" /></p></div><div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Financial freedom can be on three levels. Somehow, this post will address the three of them:</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Level 1: You don&rsquo;t owe anyone and have your basic needs met. You are pretty comfortable.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Level 2: You have enough money to afford a house or a car and pay in full. You can travel as you wish and afford whatever you desire.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Level 3: You are so financially abundant that even if you never lift a finger to work again, you will never suffer.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Most people I meet are not even on level one, and most people in the world will never go past level one. Only a few make it to level three.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">I&rsquo;m at the intersection between levels one and two. I&rsquo;m free from debt and can afford what I need. I also have investments in real estate. However, level two is not yet my complete reality, but I am well on track.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">I wasn&rsquo;t always here, though. Between 2017 and 2021, I was in heavy 6-figure debt and had to rely heavily on loans to stay afloat. I knew almost every loan app around - friends even consulted me on the best places to borrow.</p><blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Being in that constant financial panic was exhausting.</p></blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph="">I climbed out of debt by committing to financial excellence. Now, I empower others to avoid similar downward spirals by locking down money basics early on.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">1. Live Below Your Means</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">This is likely the most vital money lesson in this article.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">You need to get ultra clear on the difference between your needs and wants.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Scale back spending on non-essentials and ask yourself - will another pair of shoes or the latest iPhone improve my life right now?</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Build a reasonable budget mapping income and expenses to align outgoing to incoming.</p><blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph=""><mark>Pay attention to where money leaks away thoughtlessly. Challenge every purchase - do I genuinely need this or just boredom buying impulsively again?</mark></p></blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Your future self will thank you.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">2. Tackle High-Interest Debts Aggressively</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Credit cards and personal loans can bury you in compound interest debt for decades if you only make minimum payments.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Create a plan to pay off the highest rates first while making minimums on all balances. Explore balance transfer cards with 0% intro rates.</p><blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Consolidating debt may simplify payments too. Act fast before interest snowballs.</p></blockquote><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">3. Build a Cash Cushion through savings</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">This is the next financial goal to achieve once you have passed stages one and two.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Having several months of basic living expenses banked can prevent devastating emergencies from sabotaging financial stability.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Too often, savings get shortchanged for current fun or a pile of expenses. Flip this by automating payments into high-yield savings and investment accounts straight from each paycheck before anything else.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">What gets scheduled gets handled and out of tempting reach. Make paying yourself into vehicles generating returns a non-negotiable fixed cost.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Figure out how much will cover your rent, food, and utilities for six months.</p><blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Set up automatic monthly transfers from checking to high-yield savings until you hit that target amount.</p></blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Resist dipping in so it stays flush.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">4. Learn To Negotiate Better Deals</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Companies want your business - use that to negotiate better rates. Study online how to argue politely but forcefully. Then, call service providers to ask for lower interest rates, waived annual fees, and discounted subscription costs.</p><blockquote><p data-selectable-paragraph="">People underestimate what they can save simply by asking. It adds up substantially over the years.</p></blockquote><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">5. Start Investing Early And Regularly</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Anyone can invest thanks to accessible apps. And thanks to decades ahead for potential gains to accumulate, starting early, even modestly, lays a foundation for long-term wealth compounding can build on.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Open a Roth IRA account fully sheltered from taxes. Contribute what you can monthly into broad index funds. Getting started now lets time work miracles.</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Wrapping Up</h2><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Mastering these personal finance fundamentals most gloss over early on can make or break financial freedom for the rest of your life. Start now optimizing spending, saving, reducing debt and investing, and it quickly snowballs thanks to the power of intentional compounding.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Your future self will thank you every single day for taking control early.</p></div></div></div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph="">I hope this helps you. If it did, be sure to clap me a thousand times (joking, a few tens would do), leave me a comment (it will encourage me a lot &mdash; smiles), and share this with someone you know needs it (they say sharing is caring).</p></div></div></div></div>','https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/0*laLVZh5bQCROaDB-', 'published', (SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'Personal Finance'), TRUE, 123, '2024-01-15 10:00:00', (SELECT id FROM users WHERE name = 'Leo Martinez')),        
    (UUID(), 'People Who Happened to Encounter Themselves in Paintings While Visiting a Museum', 'Art often reflects life, but occasionally, life mirrors art in extraordinary ways. This article delves into the fascinating experiences of museum visitors who discovered uncanny resemblances between themselves and historical portraits. These striking encounters spark questions about doppelgängers, time travel, and past lives, blending intrigue with humor. From identical hairstyles and beards to eerily similar facial expressions, the resemblance in some cases is almost unsettling. While some individuals see these moments as playful coincidences, others ponder deeper meanings, imagining connections to past lives or alternate realities. These encounters remind us of arts power to evoke wonder and connect us across time.', '<div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p data-selectable-paragraph="">Art is the mirror of life, but in some cases, life can also be the mirror of art. Let&rsquo;s examine this content together, which we compiled from users who were shocked when they saw portraits that looked exactly like them in the museums they visited&hellip;👇</p><h2 data-selectable-paragraph="">Someone who has encountered his/her self in another life.</h2><figure><div><picture><source srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/0*w4tsieOfQmNScCRU.jpg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/0*w4tsieOfQmNScCRU.jpg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/0*w4tsieOfQmNScCRU.jpg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/0*w4tsieOfQmNScCRU.jpg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/0*w4tsieOfQmNScCRU.jpg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/0*w4tsieOfQmNScCRU.jpg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1200/format:webp/0*w4tsieOfQmNScCRU.jpg 1200w" type="image/webp" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4